text: my mother frequently commented to me about how unusually empathetic i could be. i always sensed she was puzzled by this part of me. not judging, but also not relating to my vulnerability for others whom i sensed to be in need or distress.  as a child, i did not realize that everyone was not wired that way.  my ability to sense heightened tensions and to ask about them caused much trouble.  asking someone what is wrong when the only measures of strength and perfection are in —no display of difficult or non-positive feelings, was unwelcome—resented.  i was the feeler.  i felt it all. and i dared to speak of it. i have cautioned my boys that the quickest way to agitate their father, my sister, or anyone in their “families” is to ask “what’s wrong? are you ok?” those ironically and consistently turned out to be fight starters, followed by confusing and painful distance and silence.  those inquiries are treated as trouble making. #empath #empathy #empathetic #metoo #ihearyou #iseeyou #connection #compassion #holdspace #brenebrown #stonewall #silenttreatment #scapegoat #blacksheep #narcissist

text:
“the shadow that roams” {poetry}
.
even when there is no one around. 
are you alone?
lost in thoughts, you are found. 
skin and bones. 
and memories. 
and sensations. 
that come and go. 
regardless of relations. 
or temptations. 
that form the foundation. 
of frustration. 
we are still found. 
with none other than. 
the permanent voice. 
resident from birth to death. 
the shadow that roams. .
.
.

.

text_retweet:
reposted from @earthlove777 -  rp @jessyforthevoiceless 
graphic footage - cows can only produce milk after giving birth, so dairy farms have to constantly forcibly impregnate the cows. 
as a result, many baby calves are born. 
since male calves will never produce milk, they are of no use to a dairy farm. ▪ 
some farms let the calves live for a few months in order to slaughter them for veal.
an analysis shows that it can cost a farmer up to £30 per calf to sell it on for beef or veal, while 'early disposal' costs just £9.
▪ 
as seen, the workers shoot days-old calves in the head, then leave them to bleed in a mass grave. 
the worker doesn’t even make any special effort to shoot the calves in a way that will deliver a quick death. 
in addition, each calf only gets one bullet in order to save costs.
(this footage is from a dairy farm in florida).
but make no mistake, this happens all over the world.
----------------------------------------------------------------------

tonight we will celebrate black filmmakers and actors.....meet @johniseeee "peezoo" bowie from the "quiet and clear" movie by executive producer @andreverdunjones as we feature the movies trailer as well as other selections. ***message from the director***
in october 2017, the same month #metoo went viral,  andre verdun jones – co-founder of the black lgbtq publication the tenth magazine and executive producer of award winning short film mr. okra – invited me to his hometown of franklin, louisiana after seeing my experimental short film dixieland (filmed in new orleans). jones encouraged me to expand on its themes in a short film. 
upon arriving in franklin, intersectional feminism was quickly becoming a talking point online and i was curious about its reach in louisiana. as a queer filmmaker of color, i naturally gravitate towards spotlighting stories of minority groups. 
making a short film that investigated gender inequality and sexual assault in this region, and that centered on the black, female body, posed a number of challenges. historically, film has revealed a white-centered perspective even while depicting the black body. i employed impressionistic principles to reflect the full interior life of the all-black cast and to implode tropes of black communities in the rural south.

of equal importance was representing franklin, louisiana with sublime images of black life; to reclaim its sweeping landscapes as a home of black america; to paint the deep south with light, shadow and darkness as a place for black celebration and struggle. --andre rangiah, director
name: Soulful Productions

text:
“i’m too sexy?” did you know that “i’m too sexy” can be a weight blocker? unfortunately, too many of us are victims of child sexual abuse and/or past sexual assault.  as a result of this trauma, the brain can be wired into finding ways of making sure you are never violated again, and to protect you from unwanted attention.  you can sub consciously hide behind extra weight, regain any weight previously lost (yo yo dieting), eat mindlessly and have cravings.  if this has been your experience,  i am so sorry and i want you to know it is not your fault.  i urge you to consider getting professional help in your journey of healing, so that you can be your best, healthiest self, in spirit, mind and body.  your brain needs to know that you are safe now, you’re no longer in danger, you can heal and overcome. ❤️ 🙏🏼

text:
my fourth grade daughter asked me about #metoo yesterday. strangely enough, i almost couldn’t articulate the ways that women are treated, many of which are emotional rather than physical. .
.
.
📖 book review 📖 
the culture of harassment and female self-empowerment is in some ways the backdrop for @alisharaiwrites new book to be released this summer. (thanks for arc in exchange for honest review). when asked by twitter if this book came before me too, rai said “before, surprisingly enough. i had to make edits after in light of that though. harassments been around forever.” this extremely well-written book expressed so much about being a working woman in america, with its compromises and challenges, as well as the joys of being successful. it’s rai, mind, so love is part of this. i liked the romance, and how the guy isn’t an idiot or a jerk. all in all, get this book on your tbr for your summer holiday reading. enough reality to make it thought-worthy, enough love to make it escapist. ⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
.
.

anyone but trump does not mean lowering our standards and voting for some sub-standard candidate. it means removing a mentally challenged, racist, woman-abusing, lying, treasonous traitor, hypocrite, chaotic, media hating, fascist from our democracy. our democracy is being threatened by a political actor. he is gas lighting this country and slowly destroying the fundamental principles and basic civil liberties of everyone single one of us. anyone but trump means living without a psycho at the wheel. you need to ask yourself, do you really want this chaos for 4 more years? *
*
*

text:
alexandra waterbury's world exploded after she filed a lawsuit in september against the new york city ballet and her ex-boyfriend, a former principal dancer with the company.

the 21-year-old's complaint described “the worst nightmare of every woman,” alleging that her ex-boyfriend had been secretly recording and photographing her while the two were engaged in sexual activities, and distributing those recordings and pictures without her knowledge to fellow nycb employees and even a donor.

for three years, waterbury danced up to 36 hours a week, graduating with an offer to turn pro. today, her professional dance career is over. "i think that’s what i would want [my legacy] to be," she said of being the only dancer to publicly come forward and to use her name in what has since become a major part of the ballet world's #metoo reckoning. "no matter how hard it is, or if it doesn’t necessarily benefit you…do the hard thing." read more at the link in our bio. 📷: @heathersten for @wsjmag

text:
allow me to reintroduce myself my name is ceo!

trenell:
trenell eaton, is a woman of god first and a superhero mother to her son.  born and partially raised in the district of columbia, trenell developed a resilience to her childhood traumas. despite her shortcomings, she was able to overcome the adversity of having survived multiple episodes of homelessness, abuse, and poverty.  instead of falling victim to statistical outcomes she decided that she would use her plights to build a platform for herself and women and girls just like her across the world.

trenell earned a bachelor's degree in sociology from morgan state university and is completing her masters of jurisprudence in child law and policy at loyola university of chicago school of law.  currently she manages special education schools for the dc public schools and serves as an advocate for children in her community.  in addition, trenell is the founder of the non-profit organization i am beautiful because, a woman’s awareness organization that supports women and girls who have been victims of child sexual abuse.  this is seed that was planted from her own person experience with child sexual abuse. "i needed a hero so, i became one"
#iambeautifulbecause #metoo #womenempoweringwomen #womenempoweringgirls #nonprofit
📸: @araredymond

text:
écrit le 22 février 2019
#metoo

bonjour tout le monde, je suis pas le genre à faire ce genre de texte, certains sujets que je vais aborder sont tabous. aujourdhui c'était une journée difficile mais j'ai le coeur gros, et ça a besoin de sortir, j'ai besoin de hurler "injustice!" sur tout les toits.

cavac joliette
450-755-6127

sos suicide
1-800-595-5580

à l'âge d'environ 12 ans et demie, j'ai commencer ma dépression. j'ai toujours été une personne introvertie, le genre de personne qu'on "oublie" mais ce sont de gros problèmes d'estime de soi probablement dû à l'intimidation que je vivais au quotidien, j'essayais de "rentrer dans le moule". je faisais tout ce que je pouvais pour pouvour être "normale". que ce soit d'essayer d'aimer de la musique je n'aimais pas, je commençais à m'habiller avec des vêtements que je n'aimais pas. je faisais tout. 
à 13 ans, j'arrive en secondaire 1. encore beaucoup d'intimidation, pour les mêmes raisons mais aussi sur mon poids. à 13-14-15 ans, des petits commentaires désobligeant sur ton apparence et/ou personnalité ça s'accumule et ça joue en boucle dans ta tête, ça n'arrête pas quand tu essaies de dormir le soir, tu te demandes pourquoi tu n'arrives pas à être "normale", à être comme les autres. j'ai toujours aimé le punk, le métal, la danse et les jeux vidéos. je refoulais même mes passions. je me refermais sur moi-même, je faisais de plus en plus d'anxiété générale et sociale, des crises de panique au point de me rendre malade et de l'agoraphobie. je commençais à avoir des troubles alimentaires, anorexie et boulimie en constante alternance. vers le millieu de l'année scolaire, un garçon me plaquait régulièrement dans le couloirs et dans les casiers. je me suis tannée et je l'ai plaqué dans mon casier avant qu'il puisse me le faire et je lui ai dit d'arrêter. cette personne a arrêté de m'intimider mais les autres camarades de classes non. 
14 ans, secondaire 2, j'essaie de m'affirmer de plus en plus, à essayer de ne plus me soucier de ce que les autres pensent. je devenais plus "marginale" mais plus moi-même. malgré tout ma dépression devenait de pire en pire.

la suite dans les commentaires

text:
♡子供のスマホ♡
娘の態度の悪さ(自分の意思ではないかもしれない)で2018年5月にスマホを取り上げた。
それを会社に持って行ったら娘のスマホを使っても周りの社員の反応がある。
私のスマホは危険を感じてから持ち歩いていたが、トイレに行く時や、1時間程度の会議なら机に置いていった。
その間に遠隔操作アプリを入れたり細工をされる可能性があるかもしれない。
でも娘のスマホはいつ？
学校の時は家に置いている。
あと遊びに行く時は大体ズボンのポケットか
カバンに入れて置いている。
もしその場を離れたとしても娘を付け回しスマホから離れるタイミングをずっと監視していたという事。
スマホを置き離れた時に本体に細工をしたか、家に置いている時に不法侵入たか。
もしくは本体の操作ではなくドコモ自体が協力しているか。
行政が動いていると言われたが、動き出したのはいつ？
2018年5月の時点で娘のスマホまでまわりの社員が監視する理由はあったのか？
会社が訴えられないために？そんな事した方が犯罪だが？
でも娘のスマホはずっと家にあった。平日は学校、土日はクラブで持っていかない。
ヤンマーとむこのそう近畿住研の関係を証明する証拠になるだろうか…
もし#andmore 当たっても私たちは監視されるんだろうか…
楽しめない…そんなライブ嬉しくない…
しばらくというかこれから先あるかわからない記念のライブ…
それを見て何になる？
歌詞を全部覚えてるか？
どれだけのファンかを見る？
活動休止発表以来テンションだだ下がりなの見てわかるだろ
また違う投稿に書くけどこれで2回目になるからね、彼女は引退したもう二度とないライブだったのに
どれだけの精神的苦痛かわかるか？
陰湿過ぎる…
くだらない…
・
・
【追加】
質問があったので追加します
・
社内ではスマホをポケットに入れてましたがメールや電話の着信があると咳払いや騒音を立てて見ろと合図してきます
どんな内容が見たいとか、早く見ろと言う苛立ちでしょう
それが辛くて怖くて最後の方は電源切ってました。
はい犯罪です。知らせるとかではなくどうやらそのまま画面が見れるようです。周りの方の反応で…
過去にセクハラで悩んでいますって投稿した時に社内の人が明らかに態度が変わり反応がありました
ちなみに会社のpcも。
私がweb明細で賞与の画面を開けた瞬間に森岡が覗き込んだわけでもなく「ボーナス上がったやろっ」と見ているよと気付かせるような言い方をしました
最低です！
・
・

walking our own personal journey towards healing and restoration one of the most significant factors is allowing time for ourselves to become healthy again. .
weather we are healing from a violation of some sort, or suffering from a loss in some way, the processing of time requires us to embrace all of the feelings we encounter and allow them to come to the surface in a safe space with the ones we love. .
loving who we are in the mist of overcoming will help us smile more, love more and eventually thrive through. . 
healing is not a race, but the work allows us to become stronger, in love and permits us to laugh more. .

text:
long post: now that the cat's out of the bag, i will share my journey! i would like to thank the florida international pageants for selecting me to compete as mrs. n. florida 2019!! this year's pageant will be exactly 20 years from the date i first competed in the international system! 😳🤩 i love pageantry, but i almost didn't want to share my journey this time on insta/fb. you see, some people don't know what you have gone through and tend to judge you, not knowing all of your reasons why.

growing up i was an extremely shy and withdrawn child. being molested as a child by distant family members left me feeling ugly, with little self-worth. it took me a long time and a lot of prayer to come to the realization that it was not my fault and that i was worthy. i am still getting better in some of those areas. reaching out and helping others has been my saving grace. there's just something about when you concentrate on others needs, it fills you with such a joy and helped me to get through the rough spots.

for my entire life, i have known that i was meant to be of service to others.  there is no greater way to challenge ones self, than to put yourself in a situation where you can absolutely do good for another human being, with no expectations.  this has also been my driving force for when i compete in pageantry because i am afforded more opportunities to make a positive difference in others lives.  it is not my time yet to hang up my glass slippers, because my work is not done and although i do not need a crown, sash or a title, these same three items have a way of pushing open doors to the hearts of others by changing lives, so with that being said, come along with me on my newest adventure, as i prepare to compete for the title of mrs. florida international 2019! 
follow my journey, as i continue my personal legacy to continue to change lives through my "dare to be me- youth empowerment" program!
.
.
#internationalpageants #iamenough #endchildabuse #stopsexualabuse #pageantry #metoo #mrsflorida #thesisterhoodisstrong #nevergiveup#d2bm #pageantry #swimsuit#mrsfloridainternational#momof5#aerobicwear
 #mrsintl2019 #mrsflint #thesisterhoodisstrong

now i, of course, have no idea if that is what @taylorswift meant when she wrote those lyrics for her song, “so it goes”, but that is my interpretation.  i find them to be liberating and representation of a strong woman who believes in herself.  can you relate to these lyrics? 💜

パネリストとして参加しました。

これまでずっと長い間、心に蓋をして閉ざしていたことを
皆さんの前で少しですがお話することができました。

性被害や暴力被害を話すことは
その時を思い出して胸がくるしくなったり
涙が出そうになったり、すごく勇気がいることです。
だけど、少しずつでも話をすることで同じような立場にいる人が
「ひとりじゃない」と気づいてもらえればと思います。

懇親会でもいろんな制度や法律の話を
佐藤かおりさんとすることができてました。

いろんな方とつながりができ、本当にいい夜になりました。
ありがとうございました。

text:
venus & pluto catch up at 22 degrees capricorn, with saturn 5 degrees away at 17 capricorn. expect ancient angst or unresolved issues from past power imbalances to be reactivated so they can be properly resolved.

venus represents personal self-worth, whom you attract & relate to. pluto represents repression, temptation(s), perceptions & explosive repercussions. at 22 capricorn, they activate the sabian symbol of transforming setbacks with grace of spirit and self-discipline. 
real power comes not from winning everything, but from level-headed practicality; sometimes the feelings of a situation are more important than the event itself. to learn from experience, be loyal to long range ends and fight irresponsible acceptance of the worst. 
saturn encourages us to cope, and come to terms with constraints; in capricorn it exalts peaceful communities’ stability and responsible leadership. sounds like the #metoo nuns movement and likely the lgbtqai+ are not going to abate any time soon. could they even join forces? time will tell.

this configuration point at 14th september, which promises to be an interesting point in time as the themes of ancestral values, motherhood and how the ‘sins of the fathers’ got passed down will be highlighted, as well as what we can potentially become while the next generation defines who they are and what they stand for.

daily mantra: “i refine my identity and the reality i create every time i clearly see what values and ideals i stand up for. as i find patterns and try new angles, great changes happen.” #gamechanger #wellbeing #positivevibes #emotions #astrology #healing #innerpeace #change

text:
bombshell thread -p1
#trump 13yo #rape
i put the whole thread together for you all!
you’re welcome..
https://twitter.com/iansmadrig/status/1068605537246425088?s=21
now that billionaire child sex trafficker jeffrey epstein is back in the news, it seems like a good time to take a closer look at allegations that donald trump raped a 13-year-old girl at epstein's manhattan home in 1994.

trump is more than overdue for his #metoo⁠ ⁠  reckoning.
important caveat: i am an activist and an attorney, not a journalist. i strongly encourage journalists to explore this further. 
these claims got little attention because the accuser has remained anonymous. but new details uncovered by @miamiherald on epstein bolster her story.
“jane doe” alleges donald trump sexually assaulted her on four separate occasions, culminating in a rape when she was just 13 at jeffrey epstein’s mansion. 
her evidence? three sworn declarations – from her, a friend she confided in at the time, and one of epstein’s recruiters.
this case was filed in new york federal court in 2016. you can read her pleading here: politico.com/f/?id=00000158…

the case was not dismissed. jane withdrew her complaint on november 4, 2016, saying she was “afraid to show her face” due to “numerous threats” against her.
jane came to new york in june 1994 “in the hope of starting a modeling career.” she soon met "tiffany," who offered to bring her to parties where she could meet folks in the business - hosted by epstein.

this is eerily similar to tales of recruiters in @miamiherald's reporting.
jane claims trump had “sexual contact" with her at four parties she attended that summer. she understood both trump and epstein "knew that [she] was 13 years old.” the fourth time, she says "trump tied me to a bed, exposed himself to me, and then proceeded to forcibly rape me."
jane claims a 12-year-old named maria was forced to be involved in the third encounter. she never saw maria again after that.

following the rape, jane says trump threatened to hurt her and her family if she ever told anyone. he suggested he could make her “disappear like maria.”
jane is not the only witness offered in this filing. a woman using the pseudonym

text: terry crews on #toxicmasculinity: “what we’re talking about is an abuse of power. there are men who really believe if you win, i lose. everything becomes opposites: men are strong, women are weak. i was a card-carrying member of that.” #terrycrews may be making big moves as the newest host of america’s got talent, but the actor and activist is still committed to stemming the tide of toxic masculinity. ahead of a powerful speech at the 2019 makers conference on friday, the 50-year-old former nfl linebacker sat down with yahoo lifestyle to talk about what it’s like to be one of the most public-facing male survivors in this movement. “it feels scary, there’s no other way to really describe,” crews tells yahoo lifestyle. “i’ve had a lot of men who are very, very angry.” crews initially went public with his own #metoo story in 2017 and has since remained a public face of the movement, even testifying before the senate judiciary committee in june 2018. but he says his message — that men need to look inward — has infuriated some males. “they’re angry at me because i’ve changed the narrative. the only way i can describe it is that there’s a movie that everybody’s playing in their head and the movie doesn’t end up the way they want it,” he says. “they’re like, ‘wait a minute, you’re supposed to beat up everybody you’re supposed to get revenge and everybody is supposed to ride off on their horse. and i’m like, nope. in fact, i’m a survivor, and the truth is sometimes you don’t get justice. you get freedom, that’s the difference.”“survivor” is a title that crews began identifying with after coming forward with assault allegations on twitter. “this whole thing with harvey weinstein is giving me ptsd,” crews tweeted on oct. 10, 2017, five days after the new york times published an explosive report (suggesting that weinstein “paid off” his victims). “why?” crews continued. “because this kind of thing happened to me.” #metoo #adamvenit
name: Jericho Road Inc.

text:
those feminine hormones that help to bestow the miracle of reproduction on women may ironically make them more susceptible to addiction. 
the latest entry in a series of studies from vanderbilt university’s pharmacology department shows that, when a female’s estrogen is peaking, she learns faster, craves adventure and novel experiences, is more likely to seek romance whether good or bad, and is more prone to seek rewards.  that makes her more likely to fall prey to addiction.

the investigators had previously demonstrated that higher estrogen levels intensify the brain’s dopamine reward release following cocaine use.  these latest experiments employed a rat model to show that females, in the presence of a light trigger, were more motivated than males to do what it takes to repeatedly get a dose of cocaine.  female hormones facilitate repeated drug ingestion.

those of us who applaud the #metoo movement see this type of information as a tool for liberating women from the restrictions of their biology.  knowing that women may become addicted to drugs more readily mid-cycle, their doctors should be particularly careful to avoid narcotic use during these times and probably anytime.

women themselves should also use this intelligence about the impact of their hormonal cycles to plan their work and play schedules to take advantage of the benefits of their estrogen peaks while avoiding its pitfalls.

estrogens, addiction, menstrualcycle, healthnews, healthtips
#estrogens #addiction #menstrualcycle #healthnews #healthtips

text:
#mybodymyrules 
ich bin nicht mein körper 
doch mit ihm 
bin ich hier, 
weil er es hegt,
das leben in mir.
.
.
.
komm‘ sag mal, 
warum 
nimmst du ihn dir?
.
.
.
er trägt mich 
durch die welt. 
und dann frag’ ich dich, 
merkst du’s nich‘
dass er 
alles 
zusammen hält? 
mein leben, meine gefühle, mein herz
und für dich ist
alles
nur ein scherz?
.
.
.
.
ohne körper 
kann ich nicht sein, 
es ist meiner 
und nicht dein. 
sag‘ mal checkst du es nicht?
ich 
darf für ihn verantwortlich sein. .
.
.
sind wir denn nicht mehr frei?
.
.
nein heißt nein
muss ich 
stattdessen
mit aller kraft
schrei‘n.
.
.
.
komm‘ sag mir mal
warum 
zwingst du mich 
zum kämpfen
darum?
.
.
.
und sag doch mal, 
ein einziges mal,
was wäre, 
wenn das leben dir
die freiheit stehle?
.
.
ich bin nicht mein körper 
doch mit ihm 
bin ich hier. 
er heilt verletzungen
doch nicht die in mir. .
.
.
.
über seinen eigenen körper 
bestimmen zu dürfen - soll das die neue „freiheit“ sein? .
(c) 𝑙𝑒𝑏𝑒𝑛𝑠𝑚𝑎𝑙𝑒𝑟𝑖𝑛
.

text:
arts in town | in the age of social identity politics world-wide shifting from inclusion to division, the recent d&g scandal on the chinese people, the #metoo movement etc, the need to dismantle discrimination barriers continue to dominate the headlines. the role of an artist and of a gallery is not to enjoy the splendid isolation outside of this mainstream conversation, but to channel, amplify and dissect the issues that drive it. artists themselves, both male and female, will respond to the debate in their own way. as art synthesizes and distills the news cacophony into its essential note, the result, we believe, will be a message of unity rather than division.
.

text:
today, we’re sharing the incredible, gut wrenching (in a positive emotion = body way) piece by johanna hedva focusing on their sick woman theory. “the most anti-capitalist protest is to care for another and to care for yourself. to take on the historically feminized and therefore invisible practice of nursing, nurturing, caring. to take seriously each other’s vulnerability and fragility and precarity, and to support it, honor it, empower it. to protect each other, to enact and practice community. a radical kinship, an interdependent sociality, a politics of care.” the theory and the piece itself explores the damaging pressure to be ‘well’ and to be ‘healed’. in the recorded lecture, they advocate instead for a notion of coping (surviving) and caring for one another as an act of resistance ❤️
•
if you have the time or energy please take the opportunity to read/watch/listen to this essay. link in bio ❗️❗️
•
ps thanks to akanksha mehta for sharing this life changing work 🌼
•
📷 @pamilapayne
•
[id: johanna, who has piled up dark hair with a bleach streak, wears a red dress and necklaces sitting in their wheelchair with their medicine in their lap. they are holding their cane and rest their feet on some books.]
name: Life Continues After
tweet_full:
today, we’re sharing the incredible, gut wrenching (in a positive emotion = body way) piece by johanna hedva focusing on their sick woman theory. “the most anti-capitalist protest is to care for another and to care for yourself. to take on the historically feminized and therefore invisible practice of nursing, nurturing, caring. to take seriously each other’s vulnerability and fragility and precarity, and to support it, honor it, empower it. to protect each other, to enact and practice community. a radical kinship, an interdependent sociality, a politics of care.” the theory and the piece itself explores the damaging pressure to be ‘well’ and to be ‘healed’. in the recorded lecture, they advocate instead for a notion of coping (surviving) and caring for one another as an act of resistance ❤️
•
if you have the time or energy please take the opportunity to read/watch/listen to this essay. link in bio ❗️❗️
•
ps thanks to akanksha mehta for sharing this life changing work 🌼
•
📷 @pamilapayne
•
[id: johanna, who has piled up dark hair with a bleach streak, wears a red dress and necklaces sitting in their wheelchair with their medicine in their lap. they are holding their cane and rest their feet on some books.]

text:
wort wörtlich 👀📰
"mann sein, sei die günstigste aufstiegsprognose in der medizin"...wie wahr!
derzeit sind 60-70% der #medizinstudenten frauen. aber nur 10% der ärztinnen bekleiden spitzenpositionen. 
zwar liege der anteil der ärztinnen auf oberarztpositionen noch bei 30%, auf chefarztpositionen finden sich jedoch kaum noch frauen.
bekannt ist die herausforderung aus karriere und kinder bekommen - gerade auch in chirurgischen fächern wie #chirurgie, #orthopädie oder #neurochirurgie. "frauen, die fordern, werden als anstrengend empfunden", sagt ulrike ley, coach für frauen in führungspositionen.

was sagt ihr dazu?
habt ihr ähnliche erfahrungen gemacht?

und was sagt dazu die politik?

ganz ehrlich: mir tun teilweise meine kolleginnen leid. ich weiss jetzt schon: vielleicht können meine kolleginnen mehr, sind engagierter, besser im umgang mit den patienten etc etc und ich vielleicht eine "pfeife". aber spätestens wenn diese schwanger sind, dann "hole ich auf". und: da derzeit unsere chefs fast immer männer sind, fällt es mir auch leichter mit denen "auf einer welle zu reiten"...
nicht gut und nicht richtig 👎
.
.
.
#gesundheit #medizin #medizinstudent #medizinstudium #gleichberechtigung #gesundheitspolitik #fraueninführungspositionen #gesundheitssystem #arzt #ärztinnen #krankenschwester #krankenpfleger #retterherzen #medlife #doktorweigl #doktor #karllauterbach #metoo

text:
i thought i was broken. ⠀
i thought there was something wrong with me that could never be fixed.⠀
.⠀
i would watch people with happy partners, happy kids, happy family - looking relaxed - and think... why not me?⠀
.
to others i looked successful, and in many ways i really was. yet i suffered quietly from bouts of anxiety and depression on and off for years. but i wouldn't let it beat me! i always did my best to overcome my difficulties, and often hid my fears.⠀
.
i have read 100s of books, attended countless seminars and sat in many a therapists office - just trying to feel 'normal' to feel like i 'belong' to feel like i am 'enough'.⠀
.⠀
i trained in non conventional healing techniques that quickly push the needle to happiness, without having to talk about my experience over and over again.⠀
.⠀
now, i want to share with you some of the easiest, and best ways to get your life on track and quickly move from abuse to abundance.⠀
.⠀
this book has already gone to #1 best seller internationally. no big publisher, no big marketing team. just me, on a mission to move us from abuse to abundance.⠀
.⠀
it's for any adult survivors of abuse, and it will help you:⠀
.⠀
- understand why you've been stuck⠀
- move the one big thing that blocks your happiness⠀
- know how to have difficult conversations with the ones you love to help them understand your needs⠀
- understand why you're stuck in a loop with money, love or self confidence⠀
.⠀
and importantly... move towards the abundant life you deserve.⠀
.
click the link now and get your 3 free chapters⠀
.⠀
jay xx⠀
.⠀
https://buff.ly/2ggmvro⠀
.⠀
link in bio.⠀
#survivor #dv #metoo #timesup #abundance #inspiration #authorsofig #bestseller #spiritualbooks #selfdevelopment #mindgains #mindset #anxiety #despression

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: i'm honestly mad as hell. went to a bar tonight i've never been to and the doorman kissed the girl before me and then came and kissed me half on the mouth, half on the cheek. before asking us the $10 entry fee and after asking for our ids. watched him do it to the girl behind me too. tried to say something to the girl in front of me and she brushed me off because she knew him and was used to this shit. anyway i got a drink at the bar since i paid $10 to get in and i told the bar owner, in honestly the politest way--not trying to start trouble if i can help it--to please tell his doorman to stop kissing girls on their way in. he thanked me and then never left his place behind the bar to talk to dude. anyway, long story short, i clocked that motherfucker in the head with the nasty side of my wrist brace on my way out after trying to explain to him (and his female fiancée) why that wasn't ok and getting nowhere but belittled and gaslighted. fuck that shit yo, i'm not here for it. terrible end to a terrible week, absolutely will never be going there again. ✌️ #assault #tw #cw #harassment #compliance #banned #barnightmares #ptsd #cptsd #mi #metoo #carpaltunnel #chronicillness #chronicpain #why #canijustdrinkinpeace

text: everyone can agree that no one knows everything. everyone is at different levels of how much information they have absorbed. everyone can agree that some people devote a lot of their time to really understand something or “specialize” in a particular subject or topic. and even within the same subject people may still not fully agree with one another but we can all agree that we can disagree about what is important to us and what we want to absorb can be different than what others may want to absorb. for example i may want to absorb information about science while my brother like to absorb knowledge of insects. everyone can agree that we are all different and are interested in different things. we can all agree that a form of learning and absorbing information is through others. an example would be a mother can demonstrate to her daughter how to hold her first newborn since the mother she has prior experience. (her experience may or may not be the best but it’s still experience that her daughter never had) its up to how the daughter listens,acts and interprets the information that will influence her decision into how she will use the information that was given to her. she may or may not accept and absorb the information and that is her choice. we can all agree that not all of us on earth have the freedom to make choices the way we would like. but we are all constantly absorbing information and constantly learning from our own experience and that of others. that is why who is around you is a key aspect of the opportunity and availability of information you will be exposed to. if you look around you, are there people who are fueling your mind with opportunities and other things you are genuinely interested in to order to give you better understanding of something? we can all agree that we can all find ourselves confused at times because of information overload and we need more time or experience to really register what is going on or has happened. we can all agree that some people may need more time than others to absorb information. we can all agree that many of us are in different positions in life with different situations both negative or positive or minor..👇

text:
yesterday, was my first experience ever in attending theatre show; medosa. 
from what i have read and been told, medosa is a greek myth that describes a monstrous women. anyway, i felt the myth itself was complicated but from what i gathered, medosa was a woman full of anger and rage but wasn't as monstrous as the myth describes. 
rebellion women were always described as outrageous , sinners, bad and shameful. they were suppressed and were used as an example to scare the rest of women tribe to not dare and do the same. 
the show was very emotional and it got me into tears especially when one women trapped another women and then rapped her head with a rope and kept shouting at her. i could relate to this very scene. 
women in some of our societies are still seen as an object. women are still expected to be no more than housewives, no more than a shadow of a man in politics, work and universities. i'm not belittling those who are housewives at all. i'm talking about all the choices that have been made for us, chosen for us, written for us. 
there was a scene in which a man tried to talk over a group of women and he was standing alone in the middle, they stood together and he couldn't finish a sentence. that says alot. i strongly recommend the show. 
#meduso #jasminvardimon #theater #shrewsbury #womenrights #feminism #politics #workplace #feminist #feministart #empoweringwomen #strongwomen #standtogether #unwomenuk #unwomen #firstexperience #standtogether #sayno #bemore #equality #severntheater #metoo

text:
よく「パンプスやヒールの靴は作っていませんか？」とのお問い合わせを頂くのですが、marikokでは残念ながらご要望に応えることはできません。その理由は「どうしたって痛い」から。もともと新卒で入った会社の営業職でパンプスを履く中で足を痛め、靴に興味を持ちました。もちろん自分の足の寸法に合わせた木型を作ってハイヒールの靴を作ったこともありますが、構造上やっぱり痛いもんは痛いんです。オーダーパンプスを作っている方でさえ、「これを履くのは２時間まで」と仰っていました。
.
就職活動や新入社員として初めてパンプスを履く方はとても多いと思います。先日も、外反母趾のある娘さんのためにパンプスのオーダーをお問い合わせいただいたご家族の方がいらっしゃいました。友人の中にも、立ち仕事にも関わらず会社の規定で7cmヒールのパンプスを履かなくてはならない人もいます。
.
長時間歩くときや働くときに、動きを制限されて健康を阻害する恐れのあるパンプスやハイヒールを強制される理由が何かあるのでしょうか。
中高生の硬いローファーや真夏のビジネスシューズについても同じことが言えると思います。なぜあえて辛い方を強制されるのか。
「マナーだから」？「その方が美しいから」？それは誰が何のために作った「マナー」なのか、「美しさ」なのか、一度社会で考えるタイミングかなと思っています。
.
当たり前ですが、女性でも男性でもご自身が履きたい靴を履いている分に関してはとても素敵なことだと思っています。ヒールじゃないとキマらない服や場面もありますよね。

#kutoo  #kutoo #ハイヒール #metoo

長時間歩くときや働くときに、動きを制限されて健康を阻害する恐れのあるパンプスやハイヒールを強制される理由が何かあるのでしょうか。
中高生の硬いローファーや真夏のビジネスシューズについても同じことが言えると思います。なぜあえて辛い方を強制されるのか。
「マナーだから」？「その方が美しいから」？それは誰が何のために作った「マナー」なのか、「美しさ」なのか、一度社会で考えるタイミングかなと思っています。
.
当たり前ですが、女性でも男性でもご自身が履きたい靴を履いている分に関してはとても素敵なことだと思っています。ヒールじゃないとキマらない服や場面もありますよね。

text:
christopher wylie, who worked with a cambridge university academic to obtain the data, told the observer: “we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles. and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.” documents seen by the observer, and confirmed by a facebook statement, show that by late 2015 the company had found out that information had been harvested on an unprecedented scale. however, at the time it failed to alert users and took only limited steps to recover and secure the private information of more than 50 million individuals.

the data was collected through an app called thisisyourdigitallife, built by academic aleksandr kogan, separately from his work at cambridge university. through his company global science research (gsr), in collaboration with cambridge analytica, hundreds of thousands of users were paid to take a personality test and agreed to have their data collected for academic use.

however, the app also collected the information of the test-takers’ facebook friends, leading to the accumulation of a data pool tens of millions-strong. facebook’s “platform policy” allowed only collection of friends’ data to improve user experience in the app and barred it being sold on or used for advertising. the discovery of the unprecedented data harvesting, and the use to which it was put, raises urgent new questions about facebook’s role in targeting voters in the us presidential election. it comes only weeks after indictments of 13 russians by the special counsel robert mueller which stated they had used the platform to perpetrate “information warfare” against the us.

carole cadwalladr & emma graham-harrison
the guardian

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
footage of nigel farage swigging a pint and thanking steve bannon and breitbart for the brexit result was deleted from a breitbart youtube channel, following the data scandal surrounding cambridge analytica.
.
- well done bannon, well done breitbart, the ex-ukip leader announces in the short clip. - you helped with this. hugely.

farage’s nod to steve bannon certainly hasn’t aged well in the context of the recent storm around cambridge analytica’s influence over the eu referendum.

it was revealed that data from 50 million facebook profiles were looked at against the electoral register, and then used to build an algorithm which analyses people’s personality traits in relation to their voting behaviour.

this data could then be used to find potential swing voters and create messages tailored to influence them politically.

the firm’s vice president at the time was steve bannon, who was also head of the right-wing website breitbart and was running donald trump’s campaign to become us president.

anna o'donohue
inews

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text_retweet:
#reposting my first post because it is so important to recognize the signs before it’s too late. behavior like this isn’t healthy. couples have ups and downs, yes, but just because someone says they love you, doesn’t mean they respect you or your boundaries. abuse isn’t love. #staysafe and #wakeup. abusers of all kind are in no way excused, no matter what. when it comes down to it, they just want power. there’s so much music glorifying violence and even murder, but really, violent and abusive actions and words are those of someone who is extremely afraid. all acts of abuse are just a way to feel powerful, to feel like you matter, as if the dominance you feel hurting someone gives you meaning. aggression and intimidation are just tactics to feel important, to stay relevant in someone’s mind and feel high knowing it. because unfortunately, since the dawn of time, it seems, people who feel feared, who see others cower at their feet, feel it translates to respect. but that’s the furthest thing from it. fear does not equal respect. it never has, and never will. fear is fear. violence is violence, abuse is abuse, and nothing more. it is an ignorance, an inability to respond rather than react. it is an all consuming, self serving priority for power and greed that stems, ultimately, like all acts of hatred do, from ones own deep self loathing.
.
.

text:
this thing i walk in has been betraying me. it marks me with its colour. it obtrudes on streets for hungry eyes, musty breathes, bold hands. once it stood for someone’s need, pinned, too solid for it’s own good. it stayed stuck, frozen, under his weight. ages seemed to pass...
.
.
here we are now, still together. miraculously together. holding each other within an inch of the cliff. .
.
.
i realise now that you were screaming too. you too were broken, emptied, filled with pain. we were both betrayed.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.#meandmybody .
.#speakyourtruth #metoo #rapesurvivor #sexualabuse #narcissisticabuse #sexualassault #thisisme #mentalhealthawareness #ptsdawareness #dissociation #ptsdrecovery #ptsdsurvivor #violenceagainstwomen #endrapeculture #acceptance #suicide #thestruggleisreal #timesup

text_retweet:
reposted from @persatuanburuh -  #repost @jaringanmuda(@repost_via_instant)yuk kita berani melawan pelaku pelecehan!
•

jika memungkinkan untuk kamu berani merespon cepat pelaku pelecehan, ada beberapa tips untuk melawan tindak pelecehan:

jangan diam: tunjukkan ketidaksukaan kita terhadap tindakan yang melecehkan, bisa dengan teriak, melotot, membentak atau mendatangi pelaku dan sampaikan
ketidaksukaan kita. hal itu juga bisa menjadi sarana penyadaran bagi pelaku, bahwa tindakannya itu melecehkan. jika tidak memungkinkan, kamu bisa berlari menjauhi pelaku dan menceritakannya pada orang lain.

ketika di kampus, seringkali kita beraktivitas hingga malam hari, sehingga ketika pulang, jalanan atau gang sudah sepi. untuk berjaga-jaga kita dapat membawa peluit, semprotan cabe, atau semprotan lain seperti parfum.

jika terjadi tindakan seperti dihadang ditengah jalan atau dipeluk paksa secara tiba-tiba kita dapat merespon dengan menyemprotkan semprotan cabe/parfum ke mata pelaku, meniup peluit untuk meminta pertolongan, pukul, tendang ataupun serang balik pelaku dengan barang bawaan kita (tas, sepatu, buku dsb). •

ketika di kampus, seringkali kita beraktivitas hingga malam hari, sehingga ketika pulang, jala atau gang sudah sepi. untuk berjaga-jaga kita dapat membawa peluit, semprotan cabe, atau semprotan lain seperti parfum.

jika terjadi tindakan seperti dihadang ditengah jalan atau dipeluk paksa secara tiba-tiba kita dapat merespon dengan menyemprotkan semprotan cabe/parfum ke mata pelaku, meniup peluit untuk meminta pertolongan, pukul, tendang ataupun serang balik pelaku dengan barang bawaan kita (tas, sepatu, buku dsb). •

text:
bollywood also needs wcc, feels deepika padukone

bollywood actor deepika padukone said that women in cinema collection which was formed in malayalam cinema can be introduced in bollywood too.
she said there are good men in the film industry. women should not become anti-men. these discussions must not isolate men. the endeavours for gender justice was not efficient. it has a long way to go. #metoo movement became stronger out of the blue. but, it is hard to change many things which are prevalent in the society. she was talking to journalist anuradha sengupta here at the international advertising association world congress on friday.

deepika agreed that she is the highest paid actress in bollywood. but, i reached that stage through relentless struggles. i didn’t do any movies last year. the reason was that i didn’t get good stories. now, i am going to do the film which unfolds the life of an acid attack survivor. 
for more news and updates, subscribe to www.english.mathrubhumi.com

text:
from one
who says, “don’t cry.
you’ll like it after a while.”
.
and two who tells you thank-you
after the fact and can’t look at your face.
.
to three who pays for your breakfast
and a cab home
and your mother’s rent.
.
to four
who says,
“but you felt so good
i didn’t know how to stop.”
.
to five who says giving your body
is tough
but something you do very well.
.
to six
who smells of tobacco
and says “come on, i can feel that
you love this.”
.
to those who feel bad in the morning yes,
some feel bad in the morning
.
and sometimes they tell you
you want it
and sometimes you think that you do.
.
thank heavens you’re resetting
ever
setting and
resetting
.
how else do you sew up the tears?
how else can the body survive?
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
abortion, lets talk about it.

so can we first talk about how both parties choose to refer to both of their positions in terms of abortion? republicans call it “pro-life” while democrats call it “pro-choice” … like ok??? both sound as if they’re trying to protect the rights of someone else, but imagine if the democratic party’s “pro-choice” stance was referred to as “pro-death” and the republican party’s stance was referred to as “anti-women’s rights”, how would you feel? let’s decide, together.

pro-life? 
well of course i would love to protect the lives of someone whose life may be taken away from them without their own say in the matter.  just because someone is growing in someone else, doesn’t mean they’re not alive.  we’re all growing in some way, shape, or form, so why are we allowed to dismiss a life based solely on a stage of life, just because its early? does that not infringe on human rights?

pro-choice?
while pro-choice argues that a woman is entitled to do with her body whatever she wants because its her body, no one else’s. who on earth could argue with that.  this is a completely valid argument.  so if there is extra tissue growing in her body that she does not want, why should she not be allowed to get rid of it?  why is it anyone else’s business, especially the government? does that not infringe on human rights?

so what’s the right answer to such a debated question? that’s why its an issue. no one knows the right answer to this question, and that is exactly why it’s an issue.  as a gay man, i feel as though i am in no place to deny a woman’s right to her body.  if she feels there is something in her body that needs to be removed, it is her ~god given right~ to go to a doctor and have it removed.

so this is how i feel as a gay man, the creation of life is the most beautiful thing in the entire world.  it is what made you today, and aren’t you glad you’re here with us today?  ok,  so like i don’t have a boyfriend, but even if i did, we could not physically give the gift of life that women can give without artificial help from doctors.  that is a gift that i wish i could give so bad.  it is so beautiful. #trump #republican #democrat #america

text:
march 23, 2019: rahu’s returning to gemini, & big changes are coming. 
read full article here:
https://t.co/pdj3aih84z

on march 23rd we are going to experience a new shift, with the lunar nodes returning to the “gemini/sagittarius” axis. this is a transformative section of the sky—the last time the nodes were here we had the 2000 presidential election, which was one of the most consequential elections in history, followed by the 9/11 terrorist event. (i break this down in extensive detail during my free webinar, here.) the leading edge of the nodal axis, called rahu, typically shows the “tip of the spear.” it’s quite remarkable to look back at the last three rahu cycles and notice the focal points of these periods, especially culturally. these placements are based on vedic astrology which has always used a sidereal-based zodiac, accurate with the fixed space, not western astrology which uses the seasons to calculate the zodiac.

january 2016 – september 2017:
rahu in leo showed the rise of nationalism and “strongmen leaders” around the world. think of brexit, trump, putin, erdogan, xi, and the weakening of alliances such as nato.

september 2017 – march 2019:
rahu in cancer showed a resurgence in the divine feminine and respect for women. think of the #metoo movement, women’s rights being at the forefront of societal issues, and the recent “blue wave” cluster of female congresswomen in u.s.

march 23 2019 – september 2020:
rahu entering gemini will show a focus on learning new things and getting better information, data, and communication. many challenges to our beliefs and preconceptions will be at the forefront.

read full article here:
https://t.co/pdj3aih84z

@elephantjournal @waylonlewis

text:
бьет, значит не любит.
ежегодно в россии в результате домашнего насилия гибнут 12-14 тыс. женщин - одна женщина каждые 40 минут. это то, что на поверхности - явное физическое насилие. от которого не отмахнуться. от таких видов насилия, как экономическое или психологическое не гибнут, а потому они часто вообще не воспринимаются как насилие. скольким женщинам приходится отчитываться перед мужем за каждый шаг.  если вам кажется, что с насилием может столкнуться только слабая женщина, то вам кажется. потому что женщина подвергающаяся насилию в семье, может быть вполне успешна и благополучна в обычной жизни, на работе и при общении с людьми вне семьи. о сексуальном насилии и принуждении в семье, женщины 
практически никогда не говорят - #стыдно, #супружескийдолг и #самавиновата.в нашей стране в ук нет статьи за домашнее насилие, это тема дискуссионная:) впрочем статьи о защите чести и достоинства тоже больше нет, это о многом говорит. до тех пор пока возможен вопрос "а за что он тебя ударил?" насилие не искоренить. да #низачто единственная причина, по которой вы можете бить другого человека - это если вашей жизни угрожала опасность и вам пришлось отбиваться. в остальных случаях это распущенность, нездоровье, слабость и неумение донести свою позицию. насилие это не норма. и не должно ей быть, прекратить насилие в наших силах.#переломвлучшуюсторону  #переломныймоментвжизни #посижусовзрослым  #приходикомнелечиться  #гештальт72  #гештальттюмень  #гештальтерапия  #закройгештальтдует #дуитёселфмазефака #психологтюмень #психологтожечеловек  #психолог72 #гештальтистка #закройгештальт #дайподую #массажкадлясердца #помогсебепомогисоседу  #легкаяневыносимостьбытия #никтонезаслуживает #никогонельзябить
name: Психология 💥 Тюмень💥 Ксения

text:
in ‘glass ceiling (nz aotearoa)’ multiple colours and shapes are seen closeup among 200 million shards of shattered glass, diversity in a sea of white. the 16.5 tonne mass fills the floor, creeps up the silo walls and pushes back against transparent thresholds at three arched doorways. the metaphoric glass ceiling transforms from an invisible planar barrier above to become substrate and structure, palpable and present, liberating and inspiring, yet access remains problematic and restricted.
.
.
.
#diversity #equality #metoo #humanrights #womenempowerment #glassceiling #monument #gillgatfield #sculpture #newzealand #art #artistsoninstagram

text:
in the time of the #metoo and #timesup movement, international bestselling author and leading global expert on mental strength amy morin turns her focus to feminism, explaining what it means—and what it takes—to be a mentally strong woman.

the emergence of the #metoo and #timesup movements have awakened society and encouraged women to find their voice and claim their power. but to do this, women must learn to improve their own mental strength. contending with a host of difficult issues—from sexual assault on college campuses, to equal pay and pay gaps, to mastering different negotiation styles—demands psychological toughness. in this crucial book, prominent psychotherapist and licensed clinical social worker amy morin gives women the techniques to build mental muscle—and just as important, she teaches them what not to do.
#periplusbookstores #peripluslombok 
#periplus

text:
【說不出口的遊戲。影評】真人真事！有血有淚！來讓一切說得出口！
李美
～
（注意，以下完全劇透，有雷）
～
《說不出口的遊戲》甫一開始便開門見山，講述小女孩odette（cyrille mairesse 飾）如何在所謂「little tickles」的「搔癢遊戲」下，遭常常來家探訪的父母朋友gilbert（pierre deladonchamps 飾）騙入洗手間內性侵。本片英文本名正是《the tickling》，國際版本則是《little tickles》。
～
香港將電影命名為《說不出口的遊戲》，比較原來版本某程度更加傳神。因為，這帶出「說不出口」的重點，既呼應了電影海報裡小女孩封口的含意，也凸顯出#metoo重在「說出口來」－－由andréa bescond親自飾演的成年版odette，不單在戲裡指證告發gilbert，現實的她甚至將個人不幸拍成舞台劇及電影，從而以身作則呼籲大家勇於面對性侵。始終，性罪行者一方面必須就自己所作之惡伏法，而另一方面，交付法律制裁也有助避免更多受害人出現。相對台版譯作《不能說的遊戲》，這裡的「不能」就不太準確了，女主角絕對「能夠」並絕對應該「說出口來」！
～
要「說出口來」揭發性侵，亦即宣揚#metoo的舉報精神，本片就很好透過多位要角來深刻探討。
～
對odette而言，心理醫生（carole franck飾）無疑是最終的催化劑，她便是odette第一個敢於突破自己、道出性侵真相的對象。
～
不過，追本溯源，odette父母豈不應該才是知悉真相的第一人？香港政府宣傳說「聽聽少年心底夢」，媽媽mado（karin viard飾）就更應「聽聽少女心底話」；若非她的虎媽性格、「有佢講無人講」不聽女兒說話，試問gilbert又怎會一而再得逞？也莫說，這位媽媽最後尚且「blame the victim」亦即「責備受害人」，居然認為長大後的odette不應該指控gilbert......至於爸爸fabrice（clovis cornillac飾）縱然是位慈父，但「有心做好事」不等於「真箇做好事」；在得悉真相後，他就對當日自己的「無能」內疚非常，甚至遺憾地說自己必須「躲進藉口裡」......這對父女在車上真情流露的一幕，絕對是電影的一大催淚位，相信每位家長都會深切感受到那種無奈與悔恨。然而，除了父親的「白臉」演繹動人，「黑臉」母親之使人扼腕，特別她在警署前和見心理醫生的兩幕，其「激動人心」的厭惡演出也深值稱讚，兩位演員皆極之出色。雖不知道，現實中andréa bescond的父母是否同個樣子，但無論如何，兩個黑白互襯的人設及演繹，於情理兩方面都大大完善了「以戲載道」的#metoo探討。
～
再說odette戲中兩位男伴，一個是青梅竹馬的損友manu（gringe 飾），一個是正經八百的醫生戀人lenny（grégory montel 飾），他倆也在#metoo事件裡有著重要地位。首先，odette的女性朋友不少，畢竟舞蹈員身份令她周遭圍繞女性，可是，對於自己曾遭性侵，odette卻沒太多向女性朋友透露－－這是否意味，女性跟女性在#metoo方面更難啟齒？而男性則對性侵更加咬牙切齒？（fabrice和manu俱揚言要殺了gilbert。）確然，換在manu面前，odette似乎才更自在、更有安全感，除了敢於坦言遭人性侵，她還會走進他正在撒尿的男廁......此外，manu亦象徵了odette過去的夢想；她去探監並跟manu一起到美國，相關「超現實」畫面便說明了manu如何有助odette釋懷，他肯定是她的精神減壓藥－－當然，她的精神減壓藥還包括毒品......相對地，lenny則象徵了未來的夢想：odette能否跟平凡的他一起到老？其實等於說odette能否返回正常人的生活與心境。本來，odette希望的是lenny適應自己的生活模式，不願反過來投進他的世界過活；但當舉報gilbert之後，odette才終於在百分百釋懷的基礎上，主動重返lenny身邊。可見，manu的心靈支持固然重要，odette沒有他肯定不成，但論程度卻只算治標；要真正治本，odette必須坦率面對自己過去，包括讓lenny接受真正的自己，否則她就無辦法走出陰霾、重見光明......（待續，劇透版二之一）
～
http://www.thinkhk.com/article/2019-02/22/33130.html
～
（影評全文，包括完全劇透的有雷部分，請瀏覽思考香港或facebook專頁，又或留意稍後的同片貼文）
～

再說odette戲中兩位男伴，一個是青梅竹馬的損友manu（gringe 飾），一個是正經八百的醫生戀人lenny（grégory montel 飾），他倆也在#metoo事件裡有著重要地位。首先，odette的女性朋友不少，畢竟舞蹈員身份令她周遭圍繞女性，可是，對於自己曾遭性侵，odette卻沒太多向女性朋友透露－－這是否意味，女性跟女性在#metoo方面更難啟齒？而男性則對性侵更加咬牙切齒？（fabrice和manu俱揚言要殺了gilbert。）確然，換在manu面前，odette似乎才更自在、更有安全感，除了敢於坦言遭人性侵，她還會走進他正在撒尿的男廁......此外，manu亦象徵了odette過去的夢想；她去探監並跟manu一起到美國，相關「超現實」畫面便說明了manu如何有助odette釋懷，他肯定是她的精神減壓藥－－當然，她的精神減壓藥還包括毒品......相對地，lenny則象徵了未來的夢想：odette能否跟平凡的他一起到老？其實等於說odette能否返回正常人的生活與心境。本來，odette希望的是lenny適應自己的生活模式，不願反過來投進他的世界過活；但當舉報gilbert之後，odette才終於在百分百釋懷的基礎上，主動重返lenny身邊。可見，manu的心靈支持固然重要，odette沒有他肯定不成，但論程度卻只算治標；要真正治本，odette必須坦率面對自己過去，包括讓lenny接受真正的自己，否則她就無辦法走出陰霾、重見光明......（待續，劇透版二之一）
～
http://www.thinkhk.com/article/2019-02/22/33130.html
～

【說不出口的遊戲。影評】真人真事！有血有淚！來讓一切說得出口！
李美
～
（注意，以下完全劇透，有雷）
～
《說不出口的遊戲》甫一開始便開門見山，講述小女孩odette（cyrille mairesse 飾）如何在所謂「little tickles」的「搔癢遊戲」下，遭常常來家探訪的父母朋友gilbe（pierre deladonchamps 飾）騙入洗手間內性侵。本片英文本名正是《the tickling》，國際版本則是《little tickles》。
～
香港將電影命名為《說不出口的遊戲》，比較原來版本某程度更加傳神。因為，這帶出「說不出口」的重點，既呼應了電影海報裡小女孩封口的含意，也凸顯出 bescond親自飾演的成年版odette，不單在戲裡指證告發gilbe，現實的她甚至將個人不幸拍成舞台劇及電影，從而以身作則呼籲大家勇於面對性侵。始終，性罪行者一方面必須就自己所作之惡伏法，而另一方面，交付法律制裁也有助避免更多受害人出現。相對台版譯作《不能說的遊戲》，這裡的「不能」就不太準確了，女主角絕對「能夠」並絕對應該「說出口來」！
～
要「說出口來」揭發性侵，亦即宣揚etoo的舉報精神，本片就很好透過多位要角來深刻探討。
～
對odette而言，心理醫生（carole franck飾）無疑是最終的催化劑，她便是odette第一個敢於突破自己、道出性侵真相的對象。
～
不過，追本溯源，odette父母豈不應該才是知悉真相的第一人？香港政府宣傳說「聽聽少年心底夢」，媽媽mado（karin viard飾）就更應「聽聽少女心底話」；若非她的虎媽性格、「有佢講無人講」不聽女兒說話，試問gilbe又怎會一而再得逞？也莫說，這位媽媽最後尚且「blame the victim」亦即「責備受害人」，居然認為長大後的odette不應該指控gilbe......至於爸爸fabrice（clovis cornillac飾）縱然是位慈父，但「有心做好事」不等於「真箇做好事」；在得悉真相後，他就對當日自己的「無能」內疚非常，甚至遺憾地說自己必須「躲進藉口裡」......這對父女在車上真情流露的一幕，絕對是電影的一大催淚位，相信每位家長都會深切感受到那種無奈與悔恨。然而，除了父親的「白臉」演繹動人，「黑臉」母親之使人扼腕，特別她在警署前和見心理醫生的兩幕，其「激動人心」的厭惡演出也深值稱讚，兩位演員皆極之出色。雖不知道，現實中andréa bescond的父母是否同個樣子，但無論如何，兩個黑白互襯的人設及演繹，於情理兩方面都大大完善了「以戲載道」的etoo探討。
～
再說odette戲中兩位男伴，一個是青梅竹馬的損友manu（gringe 飾），一個是正經八百的醫生戀人lenny（grégory montel 飾），他倆也在etoo事件裡有著重要地位。首先，odette的女性朋友不少，畢竟舞蹈員身份令她周遭圍繞女性，可是，對於自己曾遭性侵，odette卻沒太多向女性朋友透露－－這是否意味，女性跟女性在etoo方面更難啟齒？而男性則對性侵更加咬牙切齒？（fabrice和manu俱揚言要殺了gilbe。）確然，換在manu面前，odette似乎才更自在、更有安全感，除了敢於坦言遭人性侵，她還會走進他正在撒尿的男廁......此外，manu亦象徵了odette過去的夢想；她去探監並跟manu一起到美國，相關「超現實」畫面便說明了manu如何有助odette釋懷，他肯定是她的精神減壓藥－－當然，她的精神減壓藥還包括毒品......相對地，lenny則象徵了未來的夢想：odette能否跟平凡的他一起到老？其實等於說odette能否返回正常人的生活與心境。本來，odette希望的是lenny適應自己的生活模式，不願反過來投進他的世界過活；但當舉報gilbe之後，odette才終於在百分百釋懷的基礎上，主動重返lenny身邊。可見，manu的心靈支持固然重要，odette沒有他肯定不成，但論程度卻只算治標；要真正治本，odette必須坦率面對自己過去，包括讓lenny接受真正的自己，否則她就無辦法走出陰霾、重見光明......（待續，劇透版二之一）
～

～

text:
masuk ke dalam topik pelecehan seksual di tempat kerja, kevin memiliki pandangan menarik mengenai permasalahan ini. kevin mengemukakan bahwa secara general terdapat perbedaan pandangan dari orang-orang yang tidak menyadari bahwa perilakunya termasuk suatu bentuk pelecehan seksual. pendidikan dan sosialisasi pada usia dini sangat mempengaruhi bagaimana seseorang berinteraksi. di saat kebanyakan anak perempuan diajarkan untuk menjaga perilaku dan cara berpakaian untuk menghindari pelecehan seksual, kebanyakan anak laki-laki justru dididik untuk menjadi “penakluk”. hal-hal seperti ini menyebabkan pola pikir yang salah, yakni pelecehan seksual terjadi karena perilaku dan gaya berpakaian korban. disisi lain, ketika laki-laki dewasa menggoda perempuan, sering dianggap sukses menunjukkan suatu ciri maskulinitasnya.
.
"pandangan untuk perempuan sebagai objek seksual yang malu-malu tapi mau harus dilawan dengan kencang. karena pandangan itu yang menyulitkan untuk mempercayai korban pelecehan seksual.”
.
#sayneverokay #neverokayproject #metoo #gerakbersama

text:
"because narcissists can`t derive self-worth from within, they stay chronically dissatisfied. like a cup with a hole in it - nobody could ever fill them up. nacrs are dissatisfied with themselves, so they seek an ego boost from others, but it`s never enough. even while in the throes of "love-bombing" with their latest "soulmate"/victim, narcissists are secretly scanning for alternatives, and in the back if the narc's mind lingers the question: "what else is out there? is there anyone else who could make me feel better about myself?""

text: the thing that’s been fucking me up about @rkelly case is that the legal system, originally designed (in part) to protect integrity and prevent destruction of dignity, failed... wait, nah, didn’t fail.. cognitively chose to acquit over and over, a predator.. while investigative journalists reeeeaaaally made shit happen and are  only one example in the last few years of journalists doing other people’s jobs for them 🕵🏼‍♀️) i maintain my compassion for what i’ve read of his own abuse which i understand; but i cannot support a world where his music still plays (sup royalties💰) and, his lawyers still maintain the audacity to represent him. the “surviving r kelly” docuseries has provoked many, many one-on-one conversations between me and other men and women- i had no idea how many abusive interactions we, and i’d, been blaming on myself, until now. first two years of #metoo i was damning the movement because as a much of a neofeminist as i thought i was, i wasn’t. recently my dad said something about how unrealistic the #metoo movement is.. so i enlightened him with a true story about something i’d endured when i was 15, and i’ve never seen a face change so fast. the very reason it took me another 15 years to tell my biggest protector that it happened goes back to my fear (back then) that i’d be the one burned at the cross. #muterkelly #metoo

sexual harassment

harassment is wrong, every worker expects 
her employer to leave her alone, 
not making advances and asking for sex, 
maintaining a high moral tone. 
the workplace is not where employees should prowl 
for favors from those they employ 
since many will lodge a complaint and cry 'foul! ' 
because such advances annoy. 
the lawyers have entered the fray and have made 
of the workplace a legal morass, 
so it isn't a place where it's safe to get laid 
since it's legal for them to harass. 
should you be turned on by employees, beware, 
for wolves behind doors are preparing 
to make their advances and ask you to share 
what you've earned but may lose daring baring. 
12/3/97

by gershon hepner

text:
［女孩懂得保護自己很重要 因為外面總有些變態： 飛機篇3］

點解大家好似連登追故咁， 呢個並唔係改編小說而係真人真事。 我希望教育大家， 再荒唐嘢事都會發生， 任何人都可以係受害者。撘飛機也要提高警覺。 「鈴木小姐，你待會也坐 xxx航班？你的家離我挺近，哈哈」 痴漢說。 
陌生人竟把所有資料看得一清二楚。 在這漆黑的客艙 ，彷彿有一盞射燈打在她身上，她一絲不掛赤裸地站在這男人前， 鉅細無遺地供賞玩。 孤獨 恐懼 無助 。 她站起來把剛填好的會員申請表狠狠撕掉， 然後說資料填錯。 憤怒，她憤怒了。她站起來要為自己發聲！

奇怪，怎樣胸前的鈕扣被解了？睡着的時候陌生人到底做了什麼？痴漢把扶手偷偷拉起來，到底他幹了什麼？她想不起，也不願想起。還未走到廚房，豆大的眼淚就掉下來「我覺得被騷擾了」。 what's done is done 。 空姐不能把已發生的事情改寫， 如果受害人願意我們可以幫她報警， 讓法治懲罰惡人。 而她跟多數的受害人一樣， 選擇讓惡人逍遙法外 。 因為她要轉機到日本， 不想在香港報警延誤行程。

很多受害人會想，單憑我片面之詞誰會相信我？ 警察會把我奚落！ 多一事不如少一事， 反正不是風光的事 。 這是她的選擇，我必須尊重。最後，我們把受害人調離癡漢。 受害人拒絕回到原座收拾行李。 於是我跟同事走到座位幫她收拾行李。 痴漢知道女孩調走，心知不妙不停跟我說 i am sorry, sorry。 上司叫我不要理他。他繼續sorry,  i am so sorry。 我按耐不住 ： 「sorry for what? 請你告訴我，你做了什麼很抱歉的事 ？」。 他沒有回答。

身有屎的人特別心虛。痴漢尾隨我們走到廚房，用勉強英文說他很抱歉。每句 sorry ，都是戲皮笑臉似的，根本沒有一絲歉意。我：「你在道歉代表你做錯了事。既然這是錯事，為何還要做？道歉實在太遲。我要求你回到座位，並不要坐在中間位。」 痴漢朋友也不是什麼好東西。我走到朋友座位，他的頭正依傍在鬼妹肩膀！奇怪的是鬼妹沒覺得怎樣。我冒着被投訴的可能，厚多士拍醒朋友「先生，今日空位多的是，有需要坐這麼迫嗎？請你坐到走廊位吧」微笑，然後走了～

最後，看着痴漢大搖大擺落機頗無奈。二百多個客人，我一雙眼不能一眼關七。女生們，只要你才可以救自己，感到不安就立刻say no，勇敢舉報！不要替對方說話，機艙都是迫來迫去的.... 是誤會吧.... 他可能累了..... 女人的直覺很準。要相信自己！向侵犯說不「迫迫迫，迫你呀媽啦」！ #metooat35000feet #metoo #飛機性騷擾 #性騷擾 #向侵犯說不 #女生站起來 #變態佬  #機艙性騷擾 #勇敢舉報 ＃杜拜地鐵 ＃杜拜 ＃女仕車廂

圖為 杜拜的地鐵；有女士專用卡車。因為，變態佬總是無處不在。

［女孩懂得保護自己很重要 因為外面總有些變態： 飛機篇3］

點解大家好似連登追故咁， 呢個並唔係改編小說而係真人真事。 我希望教育大家， 再荒唐嘢事都會發生， 任何人都可以係受害者。撘飛機也要提高警覺。 「鈴木小姐，你待會也坐 xxx航班？你的家離我挺近，哈哈」 痴漢說。 
陌生人竟把所有資料看得一清二楚。 在這漆黑的客艙 ，彷彿有一盞射燈打在她身上，她一絲不掛赤裸地站在這男人前， 鉅細無遺地供賞玩。 孤獨 恐懼 無助 。 她站起來把剛填好的會員申請表狠狠撕掉， 然後說資料填錯。 憤怒，她憤怒了。她站起來要為自己發聲！

奇怪，怎樣胸前的鈕扣被解了？睡着的時候陌生人到底做了什麼？痴漢把扶手偷偷拉起來，到底他幹了什麼？她想不起，也不願想起。還未走到廚房，豆大的眼淚就掉下來「我覺得被騷擾了」。 what's done is done 。 空姐不能把已發生的事情改寫， 如果受害人願意我們可以幫她報警， 讓法治懲罰惡人。 而她跟多數的受害人一樣， 選擇讓惡人逍遙法外 。 因為她要轉機到日本， 不想在香港報警延誤行程。

很多受害人會想，單憑我片面之詞誰會相信我？ 警察會把我奚落！ 多一事不如少一事， 反正不是風光的事 。 這是她的選擇，我必須尊重。最後，我們把受害人調離癡漢。 受害人拒絕回到原座收拾行李。 於是我跟同事走到座位幫她收拾行李。 痴漢知道女孩調走，心知不妙不停跟我說 i am sorry, sorry。 上司叫我不要理他。他繼續sorry,  i am so sorry。 我按耐不住 ： 「sorry for what? 請你告訴我，你做了什麼很抱歉的事 ？」。 他沒有回答。

身有屎的人特別心虛。痴漢尾隨我們走到廚房，用勉強英文說他很抱歉。每句 sorry ，都是戲皮笑臉似的，根本沒有一絲歉意。我：「你在道歉代表你做錯了事。既然這是錯事，為何還要做？道歉實在太遲。我要求你回到座位，並不要坐在中間位。」 痴漢朋友也不是什麼好東西。我走到朋友座位，他的頭正依傍在鬼妹肩膀！奇怪的是鬼妹沒覺得怎樣。我冒着被投訴的可能，厚多士拍醒朋友「先生，今日空位多的是，有需要坐這麼迫嗎？請你坐到走廊位吧」微笑，然後走了～

最後，看着痴漢大搖大擺落機頗無奈。二百多個客人，我一雙眼不能一眼關七。女生們，只要你才可以救自己，感到不安就立刻say no，勇敢舉報！不要替對方說話，機艙都是迫來迫去的.... 是誤會吧.... 他可能累了..... 女人的直覺很準。要相信自己！向侵犯說不「迫迫迫，迫你呀媽啦」！          ＃杜拜地鐵 ＃杜拜 ＃女仕車廂

in 1935, katherine ripley in dallas would send empty shirt boxes from the ripley shirt company to new york, and women would mail them back filled with condoms, diaphragms, and health education materials, marked “return to sender”. this was an example of what women did in the days when birth control was illegal, to get desperately needed health care to women. @ken.lambrecht, the ceo of  @ppgreatertx and i stopped by to pay homage a few years back, because now, planned parenthood provides birth control to millions of people every year, including in texas. this administration can take their #nogagrule and shove it. people have been fighting for bodily autonomomy for centuries and we won’t stand by and let a bunch of right-wing ideologues take away our health care or our rights. 👊🏿👊🏽👊🏾this president and administration fear women and will do anything to take us back and we aren’t going. #shepersisted #futureisfemale #metoo #reclaimingmytime #counteveryvote @plannedparenthood

text:
a week ago i drove myself to the emergency room. second er visit in my entire life. to say i’m grateful right now is an understatement. ...
i contracted a weird and bizarre infection that made me look like a scary person. 😩 my entire left under eye swelled up deforming my face. i tried some other remedies to see if it would just go away. needless to say, it took a few days to reach the size that it got to where it was so scary, painful and downright i just can’t live that way, where i knew it was time to stop being stubborn and take care of business!
...
for anyone who knows me on a personal level, may know i don’t even have a primary care doctor. that’s how often i seek medicine and hospital intervention. i’m a fairly natural healer advocate. but in this case i had spider or insect bites on my fingers, swollen fingers and then the eye was progressively swelling more by the day. ...
after being a google doctor i realized it could be preseptal cellulitis, which is caused by sinus infections, insect bites and who knows what. if it’s not treated correctly it can spread to your actual eye, where you can lose it, or maybe even the infection spreads throughout your body and then you can die. ...
friday morning, the day of my daughter’s 10th birthday party i was throwing for her, i drove myself to the er crying my eyes out. feeling sad to miss out on not making the cupcakes together and getting her ready. not knowing how long i’d be staying. another personal thing about me is i’m a fainter when getting blood drawn. i can’t help it! my blood pressure and heart rate drop and i don’t recover quickly. i had so many emotions flying around. i knew i’d need an iv if it was what i thought it was. ...
to wrap this up, i was given iv meds with a quickness. it was what we thought it was. they were amazing and took such good care of me. i didn’t even faint this time either! they confirmed i was in the right place as i needed antibiotics intravenously to begin the process!
...
i just want to say how grateful i am to have both of my eyes back to normal. i haven’t trained my body for an entire week to let the medicine do it’s work while my body was under attack. #grateful

text:
🌕 watching this time lapse makes me feel the most uncomfortable. so here goes. 🌞 self-care, self-love, self-worth... to cultivate these practices takes a lot of space, attention, emotional & physical energy, and commitment. but holy shit, is it worth it... the pain of sitting with grief, carving a knife into wounds so old i was convinced they weren’t really wounds, but now i’ve opened them to see just how strong and capable i am. and wow it’s a lot.
🌕 i’ve learned that in the midst of my pain, i also feel joy. i feel relief, clarity, recognition when i allow my pain to be, when i express myself fully and don’t protect others from my feelings. in case you didn’t know, all of your feelings matter. including the ones that hurt. and especially the ones that others try to tell you are wrong or don’t matter!! i’ve been traumatized and shut down for too long, but i’m tired of hiding from myself, from the world. and so, i will no longer hide. for my own sake - for myself and for no one else - i will be. 🌑 three men have sexually abused me in my life. people i trusted weren’t there when i needed them the most. and although it’s true that none of this defines me, that defense, which i’ve put up for so long, no longer serves me. it doesn’t soothe the pain or make what they did to me any less fucked up. it doesn’t acknowledge the overwhelming fear, hate, anxiety, and anger i’ve developed. it doesn’t make up for the fact that i began to distrust the world at only four years old, and that now trust, especially in myself, is far from easy. my past has consumed me in ways i never knew it could. and it’s so fucking sad that this happened to me, and that it happens to so many people. and that i may never get the apologies i deserve. and i know that i deserve better, and that i am not broken because of my broken family. i’m thankful for the space i’ve had to open up my wounds and to share. i am stronger because of it. i am strong, i am worth it, and i am so, so grateful for the people who have shown and continue to show me unconditional love, because we all deserve to feel loved. thank you for reading. i love you. you are amazing.
name: Sofia Anderson
