🌕 i’ve learned that in the midst of my pain, i also feel joy. i feel relief, clarity, recognition when i allow my pain to be, when i express myself fully and don’t protect others from my feelings. in case you didn’t know, all of your feelings matter. including the ones that hurt. and especially the ones that others try to tell you are wrong or don’t matter!! i’ve been traumatized and shut down for too long, but i’m tired of hiding from myself, from the world. and so, i will no longer hide. for my own sake - for myself and for no one else - i will be. 🌑 three men have sexually abused me in my life. people i trusted weren’t there when i needed them the most. and although it’s true that none of this defines me, that defense, which i’ve put up for so long, no longer serves me. it doesn’t soothe the pain or make what they did to me any less fucked up. it doesn’t acknowledge the overwhelming fear, hate, anxiety, and anger i’ve developed. it doesn’t make up for the fact that i began to distrust the world at only four years old, and that now trust, especially in myself, is far from easy. my past has consumed me in ways i never knew it could. and it’s so fucking sad that this happened to me, and that it happens to so many people. and that i may never get the apologies i deserve. and i know that i deserve better, and that i am not broken because of my broken family. i’m thankful for the space i’ve had to open up my wounds and to share. i am stronger because of it. i am strong, i am worth it, and i am so, so grateful for the people who have shown and continue to show me unconditional love, because we all deserve to feel loved. thank you for reading. i love you. you are amazing.

text:
😔[ 值得‼️家長留意，性騷擾可以是無處不在‼️ ]👇 以下資料是網上讀者提供，純屬讀者個人意見，與我們立場無關，敬請留意 －－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－
網上讀者提供的內容如下：

我是一位的成年男人，在一次活動中，我認識了x醫生，他是一位的男性兒科醫生。首次見面，我們只是互相交換卡片，交談了兩句。

一星期後，下午我與另一朋友約見時，剛好再碰到x醫生，當時我們傾談將來可行工作上的合作，其間x醫生曾用手觸碰我的手臂，並說「你都好大隻」， 當時我感到奇怪，x醫生詢問了我的電話號碼後，隨即 whatsapp 我，並告知我，他很喜歡音樂。

之後一日，於 whatsapp 交談幾句後，x醫生提出一起去唱k，我當時心想，因為他喜歡音樂，因此相約唱k。

唱k 期間，房燈一直開著，最初x醫生坐著與我相隔一段距離，約一小時後，點歌的時候，x醫生坐在我旁邊，他的左手放在我右手上，約十秒時間，其間我感到奇怪及不安，但心裡想，或許x醫生對朋友比較熱情。

唱k約三小時左右，我們離開k房，在大堂時，x醫生邀請到他的診所參觀，我心裡以為只是看一看便會離開。當進入診所時，有幾位小朋友在等他應診，也有兩個護士在診所。

x醫生邀請我進入他的房間，並且坐在應診的座位，護士進入房間後，馬上又離開。x醫生用器材量血壓，量血壓後，x醫生問我的父母是否有高血壓，他說我的心跳高了一點，隨即建議聽心跳。

聽心跳時，x醫生把聽筒放在我的胸前，但我感到奇怪的，是他把手指放在我乳頭附近的位置，我感到不安，其後，他的手指更接觸到我的乳頭，由於我沒有類似的經歷，我不知道如何反應，聽完心跳後，x醫生沒有告知我身體上有任何問題。

當時我只想馬上離開，不過，x醫生即時介紹房間中貼滿兒童相片的牆，說那些都是他的病人。我離開他診所後，x醫生不時也會 whatsapp 一些資訊給我，但我沒有再回覆他。 －－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－－ 文章圖片只作參考，來源：網上

text:
【メディア流 社会課題への向き合い方】
女性の働き方生き方を特集するメディア／個人をlander laboが逆取材する新企画。どういう意図や目的で発信しているのかを掘り下げ、各々の社会課題への向き合い方を伺います。
.
第一回目は元ハフポスト日本版副編集長で現在フリーランスの編集者・ライター、笹川かおりさん。国際ニュースメディアで女性の働き方・ワークライフバランスや家族のあり方など、多角的な視点で社会課題を独自に特集し続けている。女性活躍推進に取り組むきっかけから、過去の取材での思い出、自身が感じる責務などを詳しく伺い、笹川さんの哲学に触れます。（1/4投稿）
.
◆profile◆
笹川かおり（ねこさんと呼ばれています）（@kaori_sasagawa）／編集者・ライター  元ハフポスト日本版副編集長／30代
.
q1：huffpost日本版はどのような媒体？
「2月からフリーランスの編集者・ライターとして活動しています。私がいまも関わっているハフポスト日本版は、『会話がはじまる』（conversation starts here）ことを大事にしています。ジェンダーや、lgbt、働きかた、これからのエンタメなど、様々なイシューについて、記事をきっかけに議論が生まれるようなメディアを目指しています。」
.
q2：huffpostが女性活躍のために行なっている社内での取り組み内容は？
「ハフポスト日本版は、報道媒体ではめずらしく女性のニュースエディターが過半数の編集部です。#metoo や医学部入試のニュースなど、当事者の目線を持ちながら積極的に発信しています。 仕事は、リモートワークが認められているので、チャットツールの『slack』やビデオ会議ツールを使って、子育てや介護をしている人もそうでない人も、場所を問わず働いています。他にも、生理痛の重い同僚の提案で『生理休暇』ができました。柔軟な働きかたができる環境です。 」
.
q3：笹川さんが女性に関する記事を多く執筆する理由は？
「自分が女性というマイノリティであることを実感しているからですね。自分の疑問を、記事や企画を通して、読者や識者のみなさんと一緒に考えられたら、社会が変わるきっかけになればいいなと思いながら書いています。
2018年のジェンダーギャップ指数（wef）は、日本は110位でした。男性の育休取得率は、5.14%（2017年）。数字にすれば男女格差は歴然です。政府が女性活躍を掲げても、共働き世帯が大半になっても、実際のところは長時間労働やワンオペ育児、待機児童などの課題が、根強く残っていて働きやすい社会とはいえません。 日常でも、メイクやおしゃれ、家事育児、料理、気遣い…日本の女性はもう十分に頑張っていると思います。女性が生きやすい社会になれば、それは他の人にとっても生きやすいはず、と思っています。 」
.
q4：（上記の質問に対して）また、そのきっかけは？
「実は、ハフポストのフロントページが、男性の写真ばっかりだな…と感じたことがきっかけです。
時事ニュースの主語は男性ばかり。政治家も大手企業の経営者もほとんど男性で、『この国の意思決定って男性がしているんだな』と実感しました。もともと、出版社で編集の仕事をしていたので、リアルな男女格差を肌感覚で理解していなかったんです。
それから、サイトにもっと女性の顔を増やしたい、活躍している女性を伝えたいと思って、当時は『woman’s story』などの企画をはじめました。同企画は、様々なジャンルで活躍する女性に焦点を当て、女性の働き方やライフストーリーをテーマにしたインタビュー記事の連載です。」
.
.
つづく
.
#社会課題
#メディアの意義
#メディアと社会
#landerlabo

「自分が女性というマイノリティであることを実感しているからですね。自分の疑問を、記事や企画を通して、読者や識者のみなさんと一緒に考えられたら、社会が変わるきっかけになればいいなと思いながら書いています。
2018年のジェンダーギャップ指数（wef）は、日本は110位でした。男性の育休取得率は、5.14%（2017年）。数字にすれば男女格差は歴然です。政府が女性活躍を掲げても、共働き世帯が大半になっても、実際のところは長時間労働やワンオペ育児、待機児童などの課題が、根強く残っていて働きやすい社会とはいえません。 日常でも、メイクやおしゃれ、家事育児、料理、気遣い…日本の女性はもう十分に頑張っていると思います。女性が生きやすい社会になれば、それは他の人にとっても生きやすいはず、と思っています。 」
.
q4：（上記の質問に対して）また、そのきっかけは？
「実は、ハフポストのフロントページが、男性の写真ばっかりだな…と感じたことがきっかけです。
時事ニュースの主語は男性ばかり。政治家も大手企業の経営者もほとんど男性で、『この国の意思決定って男性がしているんだな』と実感しました。もともと、出版社で編集の仕事をしていたので、リアルな男女格差を肌感覚で理解していなかったんです。
それから、サイトにもっと女性の顔を増やしたい、活躍している女性を伝えたいと思って、当時は『woman’s story』などの企画をはじめました。同企画は、様々なジャンルで活躍する女性に焦点を当て、女性の働き方やライフストーリーをテーマにしたインタビュー記事の連載です。」
.
.

text_retweet: #repost from @cecilerichards -  in 1935, katherine ripley in dallas would send empty shirt boxes from the ripley shirt company to new york, and women would mail them back filled with condoms, diaphragms, and health education materials, marked “return to sender”. this was an example of what women did in the days when birth control was illegal, to get desperately needed health care to women. @ken.lambrecht, the ceo of  @ppgreatertx and i stopped by to pay homage a few years back, because now, planned parenthood provides birth control to millions of people every year, including in texas. this administration can take their #nogagrule and shove it. people have been fighting for bodily autonomomy for centuries and we won’t stand by and let a bunch of right-wing ideologues take away our health care or our rights. 👊🏿👊🏽👊🏾this president and administration fear women and will do anything to take us back and we aren’t going. #shepersisted #futureisfemale #metoo #reclaimingmytime #counteveryvote @ppact - #regrann  #standwithpp #standwithwomen #savepp

one word to my abuser, never ever call me a "cunt" again. i am the mother of your three children and i demand respect. #metoo

text: in 1935, katherine ripley in dallas would send empty shirt boxes from the ripley shirt company to new york, and women would mail them back filled with condoms, diaphragms, and health education materials, marked “return to sender”. this was an example of what women did in the days when birth control was illegal, to get desperately needed health care to women. @ken.lambrecht, the ceo of  @ppgreatertx and i stopped by to pay homage a few years back, because now, planned parenthood provides birth control to millions of people every year, including in texas. this administration can take their #nogagrule and shove it. people have been fighting for bodily autonomomy for centuries and we won’t stand by and let a bunch of right-wing ideologues take away our health care or our rights. 👊🏿👊🏽👊🏾this president and administration fear women and will do anything to take us back and we aren’t going. #shepersisted #futureisfemale #metoo #reclaimingmytime #counteveryvote @ppact

text:
this time 2 years ago i was sitting in an investigative office.
.
i felt sick to my stomach as i shared the address of where i was raped. i explained that more then 6 people did nothing to help me, but instead- mocked me and created a safe space for my abuser. i completely down played the forced encounter that occurred almost immediately prior to that 25 year old man kicking my world off its axis. to this day- i still don’t even consider it part of my abuse history.
.
this wasn’t an attack- it was a plan.
.
as i sat reliving the harrowing details: describing how the night unfolded it was clear even my advocate was not comfortable.
how do monsters like this exist? and how did a young newly 16 year old girl find them?
.
i wasn’t brave then.
i didn’t want to share my story- i didn’t even want to remember it, but i did every single day.
i still do. .
his face- her smirk, their laughs, the smell of southern comfort, the feeling of betrayal from a best friend and the dark, twisted, denial that followed: its burned into me forever. it’s a permanent mark.
.
but every single mark on my skin, every single experience these eyes have seen, every single touch and i’ve felt- is me.
.
that was one day of my life.
.
my skin holds scars of my motherhood. my eyes have seen the world, the fireworks, the stars, and the sea. my body has felt the warmth of my children, my family, and a real man who wants to see me smile and win.
.
transform 20 wasn’t just a workout.
it was a journey- the hardest one i’ve had to willingly take in order to grow. to release. to make myself whole.
.
tripp- you don’t have control over me anymore.
and tomorrow- i am free.

text:
♡労災認定♡
・
・
かなり苦労しましたが
やっと#労災 認定通知が届きました…
#厚生労働省 にマジ#感謝 
軽いセクハラ、パワハラ、仕事の負荷のみ
あとは#犯罪 の案件は自力で話し合っていかないといけません…
いや、だからって私が飲んでるジュースのストローを匂うのは合法かと言われればクロにして欲しいですけど…
世間ではそれくらい
会社からもそれくらいでと言われました
確かにそれで労災ってと知らない人がやってたら私も思います
それだけなら…ですが
まだまだ言いたいことあるし
今日も外に出たら車に引かれそうになるし
行くとこ行くとこでスマホを持って待ち構える人
朝の8:00に出たのに路駐する車でいっぱいでした…
いつ収まるのか…
それからが私の休職開始と思っています
この会社の事件に付随して色々なニ次被害三次被害…四…五…
がありますので
それもなぜ私が対応しないといけないの？と思いますが
根っこの部分を片付けたら
解決するとおもうんですが
認めてくれない…
100億分の一も…
一つ認めたら全て嘘のストーリーを作り直さないといけないので気持ちはわかりますが…
もう私も被害が続く限りは真実を言わなければいけないですし
勘違いされたままだと
この前にアップした#手紙 のようになりますから
そうなるよと教えてくれる為にあの時期に放送されたのだと
受け取りました
私にも先がどうなるかわからない…
また#逮捕 される#芸能人 や
#地震 で無実の人が#被災 したりしなければいいですが
もうコントロール出来ない#企業 のように感じます…
いつ殺されてもおかしくなさそうなので公開日記にします
・
・
#暴露 ‪#パワハラ ‬

text:
하 씨 너무 화난다, 연극계 내 폭력은 곳곳에 도사리고 있고 심지어 현재진행형이다. 한국사회의 위계 문화는 여러 사람이 '연극'이라는 집단예술을 하는데에 있어, 일심적으로 작업하고 래포를 형성한다는 기능을 수행하도록 하는 일종의 관례가 되었다. 그 명목 하에 폭력은 정당화되었고, 피해자는 침묵했다. 이는 엄연히 공공연하게 고발되고 적시되어야만 하는 병폐다. 왜 피해자가 입닫고 움츠러들어야 되는지? 그들의 용기에 정말 감사하고 연대해야하며, 아울러 '불편한 연극'은 없어져야 한다. 더 나아가 연극 공연예술계에 국한하지 않고, 우리 사회에 잔재된 위계 및 일방적 배려, 젠더 감수성과 같은 범위까지 이르러 경각하고 돌아봐야 한다
#연극 #성폭력반대연극인행동 #metoo #withyou #theatre #theater #연극영화과

text:
nobody had a perfect childhood. we all experience trauma in one form or another while we grow up. it is during those times that we develop the foundation for how we respond to our feelings as adults. i didn't realize how important it is to get in touch with my inner child and understand why i feel or react the way i do to things until i started processing my trauma in therapy.
.
.
.
i look at this picture and i just want to pick up that little girl and give her a huge hug. i want to tell her how brave she is and that eventually she will be able to make the choice to walk away. i want to tell her that it is okay not to be okay. i want to tell her that her feelings matter and she has every right to feel her feels. i want to tell her to stop waiting to be saved, because there is no knight in shining armor. i want to tell her she has the courage and the strength to save herself, even more so i want to tell her that she will.
.
.
.
through meditation with my inner child i have begun to understand why, when my feelings are too big or too scary, i respond the way i do. in those moments, where my feelings are too intense, i have to take a minute and get in touch with my breath. i check in with my inner child to remind her that we are safe now. i thank her for protecting us so well growing up, and tell her that now it is my turn.
.
.
.
#innerchild #selfcare #meditation #selfcompassion #selflove #emotionalwellbeing #survivor #takebackcontrol #findyourvoice #useyourvoice #courage #bravery #emotionalabuse #itsokaynottobeokay #choice #selfaware #selfawareness #metoo

text:
i guess you can say i hate myself the most on days when i can’t quiet the mind... when ptsd symptoms override the effect of any pill i can find... when i fear making my way to school... when i know damn well he doesn’t teach at my school... when i remember how hard i fought to make sure it never happened again... when i 
think of the committee that decided his fate were probably all men... when i feel like a punk looking stupid and weak... when i remember what he took and left me feeling meek... when the images and irrational fears won’t stop flooding in... when i’m reminded through other cases how institutions always protect those from within... when i legit forget that i’m strong, beautiful and smart, ain’t that a trip... when i forget i’m funded by a national science foundation fellowship... when i forget that i’m a girl from the east side of pasco that has come this far... when i forget the power of my light can guide me through the night like star... i have off days where i forget i’m much stronger than my fear... are you a survivor? yea #metoo still healing, still standing strong here ✊🏽
#mentalhealthstigma #healing #ptsd #survivor

text:
jan 2018 vs feb 2019

so when i took the new photos today, by disdain was real. i picked at every roll, i got annoyed with wobbling skin, and i was frustrated with how my clothes fit. so what did i do? i left the photos alone, i walked away from the mirror and i told myself that i am beautiful regardless. that these things do not define me and i have worked so hard. to get to where i am that i refuse to let one moment shatter me. i was beautiful in january of last year, and i'm beautiful now. i decided to change to healthy habits. this was never solely supposed to be about losing weight. that defeats the purpose of body positivity. my body is perfect the way it is and i'm doing good to try and treat it well. my well being matters more than the number on the scale. as long as i'm watching out for my mental, physical and emotional health i know i will be okay. i am amazing.

#loveyourself #metoo #mentalhealth #physicalhealth #emotionalhealth #imatter #imbeautiful #curvygirls

text:
being spiritually advanced does not always mean being good to your family + friends + lovers + community. nor does it mean you are aware of boundaries and basic healthy socio-political safety and beliefs. these are things we must learn or in some cases its about things we need to unlearn. its really disheartening and confusing to realize this but also necessary for my emotional and mental safety (and sometimes our physical safety as well as we can see with monks, priests, yogis and pandits who are predators, narcissists, abusive etc ). people who can have extremely psychic abilities does not automatically mean they will be kind to you. 
in hindu myths we learn that even demons can pray to the gods and the gods will grant them boons. if you are diligent and devoted to your prayer you will be rewarded in that realm. but you may still be a asshole on earth. so... what now? and thats not gods fault. gods are not always benevolent nurturers sometimes they are just working in arts of energy not interpersonal interactions. drawing the energy down into this earth in our human bodies while being aware of our treatment of our loved ones can be a useful tool. status and advancement spiritually is great but are you still an ass?

text:
#basta de abusos en el yoga 
el domingo 10/3 les invitamos a la plazoleta enrique garcía velloso, (frente al planetario de palermo) donde estaremos dando clases de yoga, de meditación, cantos de mantras, y abriremos un círculo de reflexión-información y contención con el objetivo de hacer visible los abusos y violencia que se dan también en el ámbito del yoga, donde falsos maestros de yoga utilizan esta poderosa herramienta, (es una practica milenaria creada para la unificación con el amor supremo o consciencia universal, que brinda amor y autoconocimiento) en beneficio de sus perversas personalidades, maltratando, humillando, menospreciando y abusando de sus alumnas/os. muchos de estos pseudo maestros tienen escuelas de yoga, otros forman “comunidades espirituales” pero todos son abusadores y explotadores, y con la mayoría aún no se ha hecho justicia. por eso juntos queremos visibilizar y concientizar para terminar con esto y que nos unamos en esta causa a una sola voz: basta de abusos en el yoga. para que todes podamos recibir y dar la sabiduría que conlleva la práctica del yoga. 
además de las actividades gratuitas habrá puestos de comida vegetariana, y artesanales, y se hará una rifa, con el objetivo de recaudar dinero para el pago de honorarios de la abogada de una de las afectadas. les esperamos! solo se suspende por lluvias. 
informes:
11-65050820 -whatsapp 
basta de abusos en el en yoga - instagram 
cronograma: 
15:00 hs círculo de apertura. información, reflexión y contención. didácticas grupales.
16:00 hs kaoshikii: la danza de la expansión mental
16.30 a 18 clases de yoga 
18 hs mantras y meditación 
19hs. sorteo de la rifa, merienda y cierre. 
te esperamos! trae tu mat o manta y algo rico y vegetariano para compartir. también podes comprar en los puestos que habrá!

@yoguinisorganizadas @bastadeabusosenelyoga @vairayoga @cloledo @escueladetantraclasico @krishnapryadoula @mora.rubianes @revistacitrica @arg_india @argenindia #miracomonosponemos #mira #bastadeabusos #basta #noesno #yoga #yotecreo #yotecreo #yotecreohermana #unidas #unidasar #yoga #yogaworld #yoguinis #yoguini #metoo

text:
this spa and resort is the lush setting for the bali ista level 1 shamanic sexual spiritual retreat. ⠀
⠀
in bali-green tropical gardens overlooking the ocean, villa boreh has thatched villas with outdoor showers, three outdoor pools, a spa and hot tub. ⠀
⠀
there’s a meditation area, open air lounge and retreat centre. we’ll be in the beautiful workshop space daily, learning to relax more deeply than we have since we were children (no amount of massage will take away that armour around your heart). there’s also a restaurant with a terrace. ⠀
⠀
pura ponjok batu stone temple and kolam renang air sanih, a spring-water pool are nearby too. and you can go snorkeling, fishing, and have guided village and jungle tours.⠀
⠀
a beautiful spot for an epic dive into remembering how to be free in your body, deep healing around lost love, sexuality, grief, self love and mother and father wounds, giving and receiving love fully and deeply, feel flow in relationships of all kinds, becoming fully expressed beyond social conditioning and wounding, remembering how to have fun!⠀
⠀
the spiritual, sexual, shamanic experience 1-week retreat ⠀
16th – 22nd march⠀
bali ⠀
⠀
qs, get in touch. more info, see my page x⠀
.⠀
.⠀

text:
in 2010, amsale gualu was the first female captain and the sixth female pilot in ethiopia. while studying architecture, amsale took an entrance exam to join the aviation industry, but failed. before leaving college, amsale took the entrance exam again and passed. today, her resilience and passion for an extraordinary achievement is an indication for women’s ability. as ethiopian, we are inspired to have the first female captain; however, if we don’t work together to improve ethiopia for women, we’re less likely to have the next amsale. currently, one in three ethiopian women experience physical, emotional, or sexual violence. despite ethiopia‘s growth, 65 percent of ethiopian women still experience female genital mutilation.while only 35 percent of undergraduate students are female, female-led instruction at university are only 11 percent. #metooethiopia is established to promote equal access and work for justice to be served. in doing so, we contribute gender equality for females across ethiopia. in doing so, we fight to prove assault is a crime, not a culture.  #metooethiopa #grlpwr  #ethiopia #africa #metoo #girlsrun #it’stime #let’sfight #women #2019 #blackhistory
#habeshahistory

text:
nouvelle lecture en cours- aujourd'hui, grâce à la masse critique babelio non fiction, j'ai reçu cours petite fille! , un collectif sous forme de témoignages et de réflexion traitant du féminisme, de la place des femmes dans la société et dans le monde du travail, de leur émancipation etc. je vous met le résumé juste en dessous, c'est publié chez les editions des femmes #desfemmes antoinette fouque, sous la direction de samuel lequette et delphine le vergos: « comparable aux luttes pour l’avortement des années 70 et pour la parité, dans les années 90, le mouvement de protestation féminine récent déclenché par l’« affaire weinstein » – véritable métaphore des agressions sexuelles et des liens entre jouissance et pouvoir – fait partie des moments d’histoire, où se condensent les colères, où naissent les révoltes. c’est un acte collectif d’émancipation !
()
à l’inverse des prises de position rétrogrades et culpabilisantes qui visent à inhiber ou à opposer, ce livre réunit les « prises de parole » et les « prises d’écriture » d’autrices et d’auteurs – militantes et militants, chercheuses et chercheurs, créatrices et créateurs, victimes ou non… -, qui, sans nier leurs divergences, s’accordent pour dénoncer les injustices et les violences réelles (professionnelles, économiques, sexuelles…) subies par les femmes aujourd’hui et réaffirment la nécessité de les penser et de les combattre.
partant de la révélation de « l’affaire weinstein » et des effets mondiaux de sa dissémination (#metoo, #balancetonporc, etc.), cet ouvrage pluridisciplinaire précise les enjeux des débats et des mobilisations, et les met en perspective au regard des réflexions récentes sur les violences de genre, le consentement, l’émancipation des femmes, et l’égalité des sexes. 
#nouvellelecture #lecturedusoir #livre #livres #lire #lecture #livraddict #jelisetalors #feministe #feminisme #collectif #témoignage #book #books #read #bibliothèque #foodporn #lectureengagee #mouvementfeministe #femen #bookstagram

@latimes reports: embattled #r&b superstar #rkelly was charged with 10 counts of aggravated criminal #sexualabuse on friday in cook county in illinois.
the charges come just a week after a video surfaced of the singer allegedly #sexually assaulting an #underage girl.
the 52-year-old performer is accused of sexually abusing four #victims, according to #court records.
nine of the counts specify that the victim was between 13 and 16. one count did not specify any age. in the case in which the victim was not identified as a minor, the singer is accused of forcing #sexualcontact on the victim by use of force or the threat of force.
the charges are class 2 #felonies , and a no-bail #arrest warrant was issued on friday. a bond hearing is set for saturday. see full story @latimes #timesup #metoo #endraboymedia #news #entertainmentnews #crime #justice #endrapeculture

text:
🔴 gaze upon the cross. i proclaim to you your salvation through the son of god crucified, jesus christ. the very salvation and redemption of creation by its only creator - god made man. this grace is poured upon you so that you may have eternal life. how will you respond? turn your face and your heart upwards. no matter your belief, allow your heart to speak the words (*even if you can only muster a whisper at first) "help me father. lift me up, father. lift my brother up, father".
.
🔴1 corinthians 15:45-49
.
45 thus it is written, "the first man adam became a living being"; the last adam became a life-giving spirit. 46 but it is not the spiritual which is first but the physical, and then the spiritual. 47 the first man was from the earth, a man of dust; the second man is from heaven.48 as was the man of dust, so are those who are of the dust; and as is the man of heaven, so are those who are of heaven. 49 just as we have borne the image of the man of dust, we shall also bear the image of the man of heaven.
.
.

text:
first draft! let me know what you think 🙃🌀 #draft #revise #roughdraft #edit #editingboard

american nightmare

it's such a queer thing, really  to imagine a brain
 so small,
 so guarded  by statuesque  white men
dictating dictating dictating  protected by an all-loving god  whose warm embrace  has somehow morphed into  cruel barbed wire and mace
how has our love
become so fucking 
farcified
by weinstein productions
and trump corporations?
this is not
my  american dream.

text:
una de cada cinco mujeres en inglaterra y gales han experimentado algún tipo de abuso sexual, y el uso del hashtag #metoo en países como india y china, sugiere que, a pesar de la falta de datos oficiales, el acoso y abuso sexual son problemas verdaderamente universales.

ya sea que el movimiento #metoo haya planteado problemas en su organización o no, seguramente está en la mente de sus empleados, clientes, miembros de la junta directiva y accionistas. ahora es esencial participar en esta discusión, revisar las políticas y hacer cumplir su código de conducta. sin embargo, en algunas organizaciones se debe reconocer que se necesita un cambio.

barri rafferty, partner, president and ceo de  ketchum, nos hace estas 3 recomendaciones:

1. celebrar las fortalezas de su cultura al identificar, y ser transparente, sobre lo que debe arreglarse

2. aclarar, por escrito, exactamente qué comportamientos serán o no aceptados, y hacer cumplir estas reglas

3. reenfocar la estrategia de definir una reputación desde adentro hacia afuera ¿estás de acuerdo?

text:
urgent question: what do i do, when i know of a sexual predator in the music industry...an adult male who sexually preys on underage girls? i am personally not the victim of this male musician, but several young girls have come forward to me - because they know that i know him - and they've told me their stories of being taken advantage of, and being manipulated into sex by this adult male. these girls were all underage when this happened. they've come to me looking for help. and when i confronted this alleged sexual abuser about it directly, he admitted it to me - to my face - that he did the things he was being accused of. but he'll deny it, publicly. look what happened to #christineblaseyford. look what happened to others who have come forward regarding alleged perpetrators of sexual abuse and/or sexual misconduct. remember: i was the "villain" character of a reality tv show. i will be called a liar. he and his friends will do everything they can to discredit me, if i come forward with this information. i know that this alleged predator will try to drag my name through the mud if i come forward with the information of the things he's done to underage girls. and he does have friends in the music industry. i am torn. what do i do? who do i turn to? he needs to be stopped, and he needs to be outed. you all know me as an activist. furthermore, i may be a reality tv "villain"... but i don't lie, and i have nothing to gain. and i have proof, sent to me by his alleged female victims who are too scared to come forward, themselves. what do i do? who do i turn to?  i'll take advice from anyone, at this point. thank you, all of you, in advance. please tag anyone who you think can help. 💔
@rainn @womensmarch  @voices_in_action @recordingacademy @michelinepitt @otep @regenttheaterla 
#metoo #womensrights #genderequality #womensmarch #rainn #feminism #survivor #supportsurvivors #equality #sexualassault #notalone #webelieveyou #timesup

text:
everyone talks about how awesome mom life is... but it’s rare people open up about how lonely it can be. 
how so many times we lose ourselves, when we have kids. 
for a long time, i felt isolated, like i had no friends, like i was missing a part of me, like there was more of me in there, but it had been shut down. 
can you relate? 
don’t get me wrong. i believe motherhood is the greatest gift!  it is the greatest blessing god could ever give. 
i love my children beyond measure. 
but, it can be lonely. 
your time, your resources all revolve around your babies. 
you skip the gym, you skip the get togethers, you skip the alone time, you let your dreams fall to the way side... and it becomes a period of mourning in the midst of joy. (weird parody i know) 
i know i am not alone. 
as i sat here reflecting on my busy- last week, i am blown away at how drastically my life has changed since launching my business. 
the massive amounts of incredible humans i have connected with, spoke with, sat down with, loved on, game planned with... that fire 🔥 is blazing brighter than it ever has. 
and the beauty is... it has made me a better mom!  a better leader.  a better friend.  a better future spouse 😜 (1 day). mama if you feel any of this.... i get you! 
you’re not alone. 
and... i would love to connect with you to give you the opportunity to learn how you no longer have to feel isolated, put yourself on the back burning and light that fire again !! ♥️

text:
warning: long post

week after week, headline after headline, of men abusing their power, money, and status to demean and objectify women is no easy thing for any woman to digest. i wish for a second these men could understand the depth of what hurt, shame, distrust, and myriad of other disturbing emotions they evoke not just in the women (lets be real, often girls) they engage with but women everywhere. 
i hope these men get the justice they deserve, either through our judicial system or karma (🙏🏽). god knows they deserve it. and as much as we must punish those that do wrong, we must also recognize and reward all those that do right.

thank you to all the amazing men out there. the ones who see women for more than a beautiful face, body, or sexual act. the ones who recognize and treat women as equals with love and respect. i have been blessed to meet so many of you in my life, and you remind me, not to get disheartened- good men exist ❤️❤️ finally, to all the women, especially the young women, objectifying yourself... do your part. i am all for looking cute or sexy, there is nothing wrong with it, and its one of the beautiful aspects of being a woman. but be careful of the image you cultivate... you are more than just a body, you are a soul. you are multifaceted, talented, intelligent, loving, accomplished... the list goes on and on. make sure the world sees every side of you. if all you post are suggestive photos of yourself, there is a high chance, men will only think of you in one light- it’s not right, but i do believe it to be true. i wish we lived in a more evolved society but unfortunately we do not yet, so please do your part. love and embrace every side of you, and don’t sell yourself short as you “market” yourself on social media. you deserve much better than the attention and bad juju of the creepos out there ☺️ #notokay #womenempowerment #kraft #rkelly #objectification #robertkraft #women #beingbetter #abuse #abuseofpower #men #metoo #doright #prostitution #society

thank you to all the amazing men out there. the ones who see women for more than a beautiful face, body, or sexual act. the ones who recognize and treat women as equals with love and respect. i have been blessed to meet so many of you in my life, and you remind me, not to get disheaened- good men exist ❤️❤️ finally, to all the women, especially the young women, objectifying yourself... do your pa. i am all for looking cute or sexy, there is nothing wrong with it, and its one of the beautiful aspects of being a woman. but be careful of the image you cultivate... you are more than just a body, you are a soul. you are multifaceted, talented, intelligent, loving, accomplished... the list goes on and on. make sure the world sees every side of you. if all you post are suggestive photos of yourself, there is a high chance, men will only think of you in one light- it’s not right, but i do believe it to be true. i wish we lived in a more evolved society but unfounately we do not yet, so please do your pa. love and embrace every side of you, and don’t sell yourself sho as you “market” yourself on social media. you deserve much better than the attention and bad juju of the creepos out there ☺️

text:
greetings all! “and let us not grow weary of doing good, for in due season we will reap, if we do not give up.” galatians‬ ‭6:9‬ ‭esv‬‬. we cannot allow the things nor the people of this world to take us off our posts. we are to remain steadfast. this is a war and when we are being attacked we must hold the line! their will be a time to reap the harvest, but until then we must keep tending to the garden. the dirt needs to be turned over the seeds need to planted. the plants that are coming up still need to be nurtured. it’s so much that needs to be done on the garden we cannot turn all our focus on a few weeds. because once we come to full harvest, the fruit gets pulled out the ground, and there is nothing but weeds left. the holy scriptures says: “and god said, "let the earth sprout vegetation, plants yielding seed, and fruit trees bearing fruit in which is their seed, each according to its kind, on the earth." and it was so.” genesis‬ ‭1:11‬ ‭esv‬‬. now, when the reaping is done, you can see clearly on what will be cast out, amen! 
stay blessed and faithful!

text:
the breaking news on friday (venus day) is brought to us by tonight’s intensely potent pluto/venus conjunction in capricorn. sometimes it really feels like the planets are writing the news, and this is one of those days. since late last night, three major stories have broken revealing sex crimes committed by men in power – and all are getting the karmic retribution they deserve, served fresh by pluto, planet of reckonings.

first the handling of a case against #jeffreyepstein, notorious pedophile and child rapist (and not incidentally, a good friend of #donaldtrump) was deemed a crime. and this is also not incidental in the least – the man who allowed epstein to get off with a slap on the wrist and left his victims without justice – he just happens to be trump’s current labor secretary, alex acosta. now the victims can finally pursue their cases, after they were raped and used as sex slaves years ago, when they were young teens. next, a sex trafficking ring was broken up in jupiter, florida, about twenty minutes away from mar-a-lago. it ensnared #robertcraft, the owner of the patriots and you guessed it – a friend of trump’s. finally (and the day is still young) #rkelly was finally indicted for his long history of pedophilia. as someone on twitter said midday on friday -- “today is like scumbag woodstock.” the astrological backbone of this evolving news cycle is pluto, planet of karma, of secrets, of the illicit, forbidden – and yes, sometimes the planet of criminal acts. note that the key commonality between the three men involved in today’s news is an aggregation of great wealth – this is key.

note: 2024 brings the first pluto return ever for america, and the transit is long – we’re in it already. today’s news is a drop in the bucket, but it distills the theme – we are watching our culture transform into one of justice for all the people who’ve been trampled, used, enslaved and harmed by the men who’ve abused their power. #metoo is part of this. #blacklivesmatter is part of this. indigenous rights and the fight against climate change: they’re all a part of this. pluto in charge. full article on our site. photo: moon glow by brenda erickson
name: Saturnsisters

text:
lessons learned 4 - it wasn't my fault... or was it? as i walked back to my desk, i held my mug in my hand but my fingers were shaking in anger.
.
any more than this and my coffee will spill. get a grip, girl!
.
why do men feel like they have to pass a comment about everything?
.
i went to the kitchen to make myself a cup of coffee and walked in on a group of men talking about the super bowl.
.
then i heard it - that awfully local whistle (a.k.a "cat call"), from someone with absolutely no home training or chivalry.
.
"young lady, i am sure you look into the mirror every day and thank god" "good morning sir. doesn't everybody thank god?" i replied. "but your own should be special thanks. you have very nice bodily assets that any woman would envy".
.
pin drop silence. all eyes on me.
.
i could feel them scan my body from head to toe. can the earth just open up and swallow me now!
.
i was wearing decent clothes -  a calf length skirt and loosely fitted blouse.
.
no. my button wasn't open, neither was my blouse cut low.
.
i didn't ask for this, i just wanted a cup of coffee.
.
no! it is not my fault so don't even go there.
.
or was it?
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
“my name is cecibel contreras, i am a child advocate, mentor and an author. i’m also the founder of it was me campaign and incest survivors united voices of america, two non-profit organizations dedicated to spreading awareness about sexual abuse and to provide support and resources for both male and female survivors that have been affected by childhood sexual abuse.

healing and recovery is a challenging process, but it is not an impossible one. you may suffer for a very long time from intrusive thoughts, flashbacks and other symptoms as a result of the sexual abuse but you must continue to press forward and walk the healing journey. i began my healing journey by sharing my story on a blogger and even though sharing my story brought a lot of pain, it also empowered me to know that i wasn’t alone and that i could heal and become the rockstar that i am now.” cecibel from @embracing_the_beauty_in_me is a rockstar and a survivor of sexual trauma and human trafficking.  read her story: https://iamarockstar.me/portfolio-items/cecibel-contreras/

text:
✧ flashbacks: part 4 ✧ in the last three segments, we've learned all about flashbacks: what they are, who they affect, how they present, and the various types. now it's time to talk coping. how does one begin to combat a flashback and deliver themselves safely into the calm present? unfortunately, some of the best, failproof tools can take a lot of time to learn and require ample practice and high levels of specificity. and, whether you've just begun your healing journey or are a decade-long veteran, there are some flashbacks that make it hard to remember what's even happening to you or that skills are a thing that exist in the world. being able to call upon really detailed symptom management can be all but impossible. because of this, we wanted to compile a list of four very simple, easy-to-learn, easy-to-use skills that can help you more confidently tackle even the most disorienting flashback. and, you can use these while learning, customizing and beginning to practice the more involved skills, always knowing you have a solid foundation to rely on. you aren't helpless. you've got this.
.
🌿🌳
use the link in bio or head to: beautyafterbruises.org/blog/flashbacks
🌳🌿
.
we sincerely hope this "starter kit" for managing flashbacks is helpful regardless where you're at in your recovery. these tools can also be helpful for loved ones, supporters, and therapists to be well-versed in because there are times in a survivor's life where doing it alone is just too tall an order. having someone else there to walk them through can not only be exactly what they need but also be a very corrective experience.
.
we are thinking of you all and hope that your future symptoms are much less distressing and that you soon replace that feeling with one of mastery, competence and security.
.
☁️🌳☀️
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
when i was younger i was afraid of my own femininity- worried it would be used against me. inner child work means going back and rewriting these types of stories. when we have the courage to go back and fiercely love these parts of ourselves that may seem broken or taken away we can reclaim and repair so that we can bloom again. it also helps to be surrounded by women who are able to fearlessly hold space. this is what radical self love looks like, i wish it for all of you! this grid is for all of us. resting in gratitude for all the love and support within and all around!
✨💞🌸💞✨

text:
“i’m emily, a rockstar, and i’m on a mission to support survivors in living more than a half-life, coping one day at a time, and to live instead a full and whole reconnected life. i have used my experience and the skills i developed in my recovery to create a pathway to living reconnected that goes beyond merely managing our symptoms from the trauma. i am on a mission to challenge and change the untrue myths that say we will be forever broken and to address trauma recovery from a whole-person holistic perspective. i’m also on a mission to end rape culture, and to speak up for survivors every opportunity i get, so you can often find me writing or speaking in the public sphere to break the silence and change the world. i’m a coach, an nlp master practitioner, an author, a blogger, a speaker, a community leader, a survivor: i’m a rockstar”
– emily

emily is a survivor of sexual trauma. 
read more about emily, share your rockstar story and find resources at our website. 
link in bio.
you can also check out emily’s website at reconnect.life
#iaar

mientras escribía esto, pasó un hombre en un coche y me preguntó qué estaba haciendo. le expliqué que era para luchar contra el acoso callejero. me dijo: ¿acoso callejero? le digo: sí, existe. esto se lo dijo el otro día un hombre a una niña que iba al instituto por la mañana. él miró el mensaje y me dijo: pero eso no es malo, ¿no? le dije: la niña nunca le pidió su opinión, el hombre no le debería haber dicho nada. además tenemos que tener en cuenta que es una niña por la mañana yendo al instituto y un hombre mucho más mayor haciéndole comentarios impropios e indeseados, es acoso callejero. me dijo: ahh vale, suerte! y se fue.
la mayoría (por suerte no todos) de los hombres no están muy enterados del feminismo, son víctimas del hetero patriarcado y se les ha enseñado, como pensaba este hombre, que comentarios así están dentro de lo normal. bien es verdad que muchos podrían luchar por abrir los ojos, darse cuenta de que esto es horrible, pero mientras tanto, es nuestro papel enseñarles, explicarles que hay cosas que aunque vengan definidas como normales y por lo tanto buenas, no son para nada éticas. más que enseñar a las mujeres a no ser violadas, tenemos que enseñar a los hombres a no violar. la lucha es nuestra, conciencia a tu padre, tu hermano, tu novio, tu familia, tu hijo, tus amigos, tu entorno, etc. luchemos por una educación inclusiva que haga que dentro de un tiempo esta cuenta y muchas otras más ni sean necesarias.
-

text:
i take no delight in seeing anyone enter the criminal justice system, because it is punitive and rarely provides rehabilitation or a second chance at life. i especially take no delight in seeing a brilliant black man go to jail.

yet, i have been triggered by the total disregard of black girls in chicago and the continued victim shaming and blaming. it relates directly to the total disregard i have felt as a black woman in america.

i am tired of feeling as if i don’t matter and must constantly prove that i do. i now know it isn’t just a feeling, it’s an epidemic.

but today, my heart is so full!

dream hampton, and every last woman who agreed to have their stories taped are today’s black history and women’s history sheroes. kim foxx became state’s attorney and today uses her platform to bring charges that her predecessors were unable to bring.

what did they do? they advocated for themselves. they worked their way up to a level where they could affect change and then did so. 
black women. you are brilliant and deserving of protection. you must continue to advocate for yourselves. your bodies are beautiful and sacred.

when no one listens to you, persist!

#advocateforyourself #stopvictimshaming #thankyou #blackgirlmagic #metoo #sexualtrauma #rape

text:
chicago prosecutors have charged r&b star r. kelly with 10 counts of aggravated sexual abuse, according to media reports citing court records.

friday's charges come after years of allegations directed at kelly, accusing the now 52-year-old of sexual misconduct involving women and underage girls. through his lawyers, he has consistently denied them.
kelly, whose legal name is robert kelly.

jurors acquitted kelly of child pornography charges at a 2008 trial. those charges stemmed from a video prosecutors alleged showed kelly having sex with a girl as young as 13.
attorney michael avenatti said last week that he recently gave chicago prosecutors new video evidence of kelly having sex with an underage girl.

attorney michael avenatti says he has evidence r. kelly and his "enablers" paid witnesses and others to "rig" the outcome of the r&b star's 2008 trial, when he was acquitted on child pornography charges.
#timesup #metoo #rkelly predator

🤗i am not part of the #metoo movement. however i will never be silent about the #inequality and #injustice towards #women. i have personally experienced it many times in my social, personal, and business life. because i am a women, people have force their thinking on me, their boundaries on me my whole life. they will tell you how to dress, how to behave, who you can meet and where you can go, and overall how they think women should be. don't live in the shadows of people's #judgement and ideas. make your own choices in the light of your own #wisdom. if you can't make the decision then go to someone close to you, let them be your #soundboard and communicate. 👩🏻‍💻👩‍🏫👩🏼‍🎓👩🏿‍⚕️👩🏽‍⚖️👩🏼‍🌾🧕👩🏻‍🍳👩🏼‍🏭👩🏻‍🚀👩🏾‍💼👰🏽👩🏽‍🔧👩‍🔬👩🏼‍🎤👩🏻‍✈️👩🏿‍🎨👩🏾‍🚒👸🏻

text:
for ballet’s foremost #metoo accuser, a second act
#
alexandra waterbury’s posture is perfect. it’s the kind people beg their yoga teachers to make possible. the dancer, 21, lifts her chin in a way that unfurls her 5-foot-9-inch frame to its fullest. with her watery blue eyes and long blond hair, she looks like a music-box ballerina in a cream turtleneck. for three years, waterbury practically lived at lincoln center, dancing up to 36 hours a week at the school of american ballet (new york city ballet’s affiliate academy) and graduating with an offer to turn pro with the washington ballet. today, her professional dance career is over. she’s now midway through her second year of college at columbia university, and at this moment, fresh from a visit to her statistics tutor. she flops down a large black tote bag, the urban staple for women with one foot in young-adult lives and another in professional ones. “i feel like kids on disney channel,” she says of the life she now wants to avoid. “they grow up with this immense pressure to be perfect all the time. and that’s when things explode.” waterbury’s own world exploded after she filed a lawsuit in september against nycb and her ex-boyfriend chase finlay,…

text:
i'm the girl who had her nose broken so many times she lost count. going from abuse to abuse, trauma to trauma, brokenness to brokenness. doing the hard work of healing doesn't  always look so pretty. this year to finally be in a place of true peace internally true joy spiritually and mentally it feels so good.  i'm true believer in the wondrous power of god's love and forgiveness. learning to love and forgive self and learning to love and forgive others is essential to walking in freedom. 
i've always been a giving person but to give without my own internal baggage what a blessing it has been. to be able to help others in there journey is just so rewarding. #grateful #loveandforgive #wholeselfhealing #beinspired #youcandoit #overcomer #metoo #blessedandhighlyfavored #yesican #anythingispossible #believeandrecieve

it takes one voice to inspire others. and before that, it takes someone to believe our #fearlessfox this friday is tarana burke @taranajaneen
•
burke was assaulted both as a child and a teenager. her mother supported her recovery from these violent acts and encouraged her to be involved in the community, helping young girls going through extreme hardships.
•
#metoo changed society and it changed the way victims were able to move forward from emotional scars. because of this movement, there is awareness, there is community, there is less shame and more opportunity for women to live their lives fully, and we couldn't be more thankful for how she’s turned her own darkness into light for so many others.
